After 15 minute observation period, pt. began feeling dizzy and lightheaded while she was enroute to parking area via golf cart accompanied by her mother and a staff member.  Staff member returned pt. to clinic for evaluation, she arrived to clinic at 11:15. Note: Patient speaks fluent English, however a staff member interpreted encounter in Spanish at pt?s request for benefit of her mother.  11:15:  VS (lying):  BP 100/70, P 92, SpO2 99% - c/o dizziness and thirst.  Reports she actually felt transient lightheadedness when she walked out of clinic to golf cart originally.  Has eaten only a small bowl of cereal today.  Skin pale, dry, no rashes, hives, lesions.  No swelling of face, mouth, oropharynx, or neck.  No respiratory distress, lungs clear.   11:20:  Feels better after lying down, drinking water and eating a cracker. Dizziness resolved, still slightly lightheaded with sitting up. Color normal per mother. No swelling of face, mouth, or neck.  No respiratory distress.   11:24:  VS (sitting): BP 110/62, P 88.  Feels ?okay? and wants to go home.   11:30:  VS (standing):  BP 96/68, P 96.  Became dizzy, lightheaded and pale with standing.  Remains oriented x 4, but verbal responses slowed.  No speech deficits, moving all extremities, PERL.  No syncope, LOC, seizure activity.   11:32:  P 98, R 14, SpO2 93%. Remains pale with slowed verbal responses.  No swelling of face, mouth, or neck.  No respiratory distress. Encouraged to take deeo breaths.  EMS called. 11:34: Pallor and rapidity of verbal responses slowly improving upon lying down.   11:37:  VS BP 110/80, P 110, R 15, SpO2 98%.   11:40:  EMS arrived, assessed patient, including repeat orthostatic VS (normal), EKG, and RBG.  Pt. reports she feels better and wants to go home.   11:55:  EMS assessment complete ? pt reports dizziness resolved, states ?just feel tired now?. Wants to go home, declines transport to ED.  Given DC instructions to rest, monitor for side effects, when to call 9-1-1. 12:00:  To car with mother via golf cart with staff member.
LAB_DATA: 5/7/2021:  Orthostatic VS, EKG = NSR, and RBG = 85 mg/dL

Got shot on a Tuesday 3pm, arm sore right away, full body aches appeared 12 hours after. I woke up Thursday morning with a left swollen labia minora and a stinging sharp pain wiping after urination, blood spots on TP. I took flash photos to see what it looked like at the entrance of my vagina. I saw a cluster of small, bleeding, open wound sores, looked like speckles of blood. I saw a doctor at Health Services the next morning and was told it looks like I have herpes. I did a viral culture swab for hsv. I had just tested negative for a full panel std test (minus hsv) in February, so we did not redo it. Monday, I got the call, my doctor said the results were negative and most likely a false negative, she said she is sure I have herpes. Tuesday, the next day I go into health services again to get a second opinion from another doctor and get re-swabbed. The second doctor agreed it looks just like herpes and she doesn't know what else it could be. We do another viral culture swab and she confirmed that she picked up fluid from the sores this time. I was also swabbed for gonorrhea and chlamydia and redid the full panel std blood test from February. The results all come back negative, and the doctor says she doesn't know what else it could be besides herpes. I am fed up with no answers and go to an urgent care. The doctor does not know what my lesions could be from. We did another viral culture swab that tests for gonorrhea and chlamydia and hsv. She offered pills to treat chancroid just in case and I took them thinking it was risk free. By the time I got home I was throwing up for a couple hours. My results come back negative. My second doctor calls me and says she is confident I could have syphilis (even though the sores were the most pain I've ever experienced). I came in to give blood for syphilis and hsv testing. Both came back negative, but the doctor was telling me I should still go somewhere for syphilis treatment (a shot I think?). I was even more frustrated.  I sought out an OBGYN center that specializes in ulcers. The amazing doctor agreed with me that I do not have any std's and that my ulcers were a result of the vaccine. By this time the sores were healed.
LAB_DATA: 3 viral cultural std swabs 2 std blood tests lidocaine 2% & 5% valtrez 1000mg twice a day for 10 days Azithromycin 4 pills one visit

By May 7 10:05 I called off of work to go my doctor, because I had massive splotches of raised itchy hives all over my body. Autoimmune encephalitis vs Listeria infection - 78 yo F with encephalitis. Second Moderna vaccine on 3/6/2021, admitted on 3/31/2021.    4/18 IM Progress NOTE states: #Limbic encephalitis, improving. Treating for Listeria given inflammatory findings in addition to lymphocytic CSF and few gram-positive cocci on stain. CSF paraneoplastic antibodies are negative therefore anticipating that the serum antibodies will also come back negative Depressed flat affect consistent with limbic inflammation -improving Repeat MRI 4/14 shows improvement Ampicillin, tentative plan for 4 to 8 week course for possible listeriosis Gentamicin, completed 1 week course 4/15. Continues on Keppra                                                                                                        4/20 Neurology Progress NOTE: Impression - Meningoencephalitis, presumed to be secondary to listeria.                                                                                                              4/27 ID progress NOTE : Patient found to have limbic encephalitis and possible infectious cerebritis.  CSF exam, was performed after about 2.5 days of antibiotics due to patient anticoagulation, showed 27 white blood cells, 96% lymphocytes; protein 146, glucose 69.  Meningitis encephalitis PCR panel negative.  Gram stain with rare intracellular GPC's, culture negative. Per micro lab, 2 different techs each visualized 2 different fields with an intracellular GPC.  Clinical picture was thought compatible with Listeria (which is a bacillus, but could be mistaken for a coccus).  Completed 10 days of empiric vancomycin and ceftriaxone on 4/10.  was on ampicillin CNS dosing, plus gentamicin for synergy started 4/9, now off of gentamicin.  Ampicillin changed to meropenem due to drug eruptions.  Continued slow clinical improvement; repeat MRI brain 4/13 showed radiographic improvement.  Noted to have negative coccidioides serology but not titre came back at 1:8, repeat titre negative.  Repeat LP shows similar findings with 28 WBCs, with lymphocytic predominant, slightly low glucose and elevated protein.  Awaiting Coccidioides CSF and fungal cultures.  Continue fluconazole 400 mg daily, renally adjusted.  No evidence of QTc prolongation.  Continue to monitor rash. No evidence of DRESS, TENS or SJS. Patient has eosinophiluria.  Continue current plan of care.  Diagnosis:  -Limbic encephalitis  -Positive coccidioides titre of 1:8  -Possible infectious cerebritis  -Rash and pruritus - improving.  -Breast cancer in remission s/p mastectomy, radiation, chemotherapy  -Atrial fibrillation with RVR  -AKI with eosinophiluria Discharged on 4/27/21
HISTORY: Breast cancer status post mastectomy. Skin cancer. Cataract surgery. Hysterectomy. Atrial fibrillation. Hypertension. Hyperlipidemia. Sleep apnea.
ALLERGIES: LEVAQUIN. TAPE. IODINATED RADIOCONTRAST DYES. TOPICAL IODINE. PENICILLIN. TETRACYCLINE.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: At 2:54 pm, the patient received her first dose of Pfizer (lot number EW0179, expires on 08/2021) on left deltoid. Patient walked with a steady, balanced gait to EMT observation area. At 3:20 pm, patient notified EMT that she was feeling unwell. Patient became diaphoretic. EMT assisted patient to anti-gravity chair. Patient remained A&Ox4 and talking to EMT. Patient complained of chills in back of neck and numbness in hands bilaterally. Lead RN was notified of reaction. RN requested vitals Q5 minutes for 30 minutes. At 3:24 pm: BP of 120/80, HR 107, SPO2 99% and respirations of 17/min. Patient's husband was notified and he sat with patient. Patient consumed 16 oz of water. At 3:29 pm, patient reports no longer experiencing numbness in hands. At 3:30 pm: 130/80, SPO2 99%, HR 92, RR 17. Patient no longer diaphoretic. Patient states she is "feeling better" and requested to leave facility. Patient was A&Ox4 with no reports of dizziness and lightheadedness. Lead RN provided patient with education concerning when to call 9-1-1, including worsening of symptoms and trouble breathing. Patient was instructed to follow up with PCP. At 3:35 pm, patient stood up from chair, denied lightheadedness and dizziness. Patient walked to car with steady, balanced gait.

Approximately five minutes after shot, my face began to tingle. My heart felt like it was racing. I had difficulty focusing with my eyes, it felt like my eyes were rolling.  My feet began to tingle. My spouse honked the car horn for assistance. I reached for my epi pen but did not administer it because a doctor was approaching our car. I checked my pulse rate on my iWatch, it was 168.  My throat began to feel tight. The doctor listened to my lungs and heard wheezing. A paramedic came over as well. My blood pressure was taken but I do not remember what my blood pressure was.  At that point the doctor said I should use my epi pen. The paramedic said I should use Benadryl. They were in disagreement, and the paramedic said I should take 50mg of Benadryl and had me put my car seat in recline position.  It was at the point they noticed that my face and chest were flushed.  They had me drink water.  We waited about 45 minutes. My lungs were checked again by the paramedic and I was told my lungs were clear, my blood pressure was taken second time but I do not remember my blood pressure, my face was less flush,  my pulse was in the 70?s.  I still felt tingling on my scalp and feet, my throat felt like it had a lump in it.  I Began to feel nauseous.  I was given the okay to leave and go home.  I had nausea until the evening the next day.  I did not eat until dinner time the night after my shot.  I only drank water.  The next day I experienced shortness of breath performing  duties that typically do not make me out of breath.  I had to take many breaks and used my abuterol inhaler two times.

Patient stood up while we continued to talk, after 2 more minutes passed out while standing. Suddenly, patient begain to go limp and her eyes crossed and rolled back. Patient fell backwards into the privacy curtain and into aisle 13 of the store. Patient's head bounced off the floor. Immunizer  knelt next to patient. Patient was unresponsive until immunizer placed cold hand on back of neck and front of chest to check if she was breathing, immunizer calmly  guided patient to breath, slow deep breaths into the belly and patient's eyes fluttered open. She said her head hurt really bad. Immunizer offered to the accompanying adult to call EMS because patient should be evaluated after hitting her head so hard. The accompanying adult denyed EMS, then stating that patient had previously fainted while walking and said that she would be fine. Immunizer advised patient to remain laying down while immunizer got some ice. Ice was then placed on the back of the head. Patient slowly stood up after laying for 10 minutes and was walked over to a sitting area to put feet up and continue with ice for another 5 minutes before the accomanying adult wanted to leave.

I had my first Covid19 Moderna shot on 4/1/21. Second day I had a sore arm (not an unusual side effect) but throughout the weeks after I realized my legs were tingling. My legs felt swollen (when pressed on the skin, you could see white imprint as if there was excessive water). I particularly felt my knees being swollen, almost sore. Noticed that my legs felt little numb (as if they were made out of wood?). Long walks (and I walk a lot) tired my legs more easily.  Had my second Covid 19 Moderna shot on 5/6/21. Once again I had a sore arm. About 24 hours after the vaccine, both my arms and legs were tingling. Legs felt more numb. The tingling in arms went from tip of fingers to top of shoulders. The tingling in my arms went from my feet all the way up to my waist. The sensation was definitely more intense than what I experienced after the first shot. About 1 hour after the tingling started, I checked my fever and had 100.5 F. The fever lasted 6 hours along with the tingling/numbness. After 6 hours, I can only feel little bit of tingling in my legs and a "heavy" feeling in my knees.

12 hrs after shot  felt exhaustion, mental brain fog, mild nausea and migraines.  In the weeks following vaccine, exhaustion and migraines have persisted at an interval of several times a week. This is abnormal for me - i do not have headaches regularly or migraines.  It has almost been 2 months and I am still having exhaustion and migraines.

I immediately felt lightheaded and dizzy. My head started pounding and I had my partner help me walk to the car. I couldn't drive my car, so he drove us home. I thought I'd wait it out, but the symptoms only got worse. After about an hour I started feeling nauseous. I couldn't stand up as I would get dizzy every time I tried. After a couple hours, I tried to eat, but ended up throwing up shortly after. My whole body just did not feel right. I went to the urgent care clinic the next morning. The doctor said it's a vaccine reaction, or some sort of allergic reaction to the vaccine. She said it will pass, but if I feel out of breath to go to the hospital immediately. The symptoms continued for a few days, and I had to off a couple days of work. I was so dizzy and lightheaded for a total of 5 days. I was also very nauseous and could only eat small amounts of soup. I felt extremely tired, and spent most of the time in bed or laying on the couch. One the fifth day, symptoms started to gradually get better. I went to work on day 6, but spent that whole week sitting at my desk feeling extremely fatigued. After about 10 days, symptoms were gone.
LAB_DATA: Went to the urgent care clinic and got examined by a doctor.

While she was in the hospital she was admitted to the stroke unit, received serial CT and MRI which did not show ischemia or brain bleed, Neurology gave her IV tPA and had her admitted for observation. Several hours after receiving tPA she steadily started improving (left-sided weakness and headaches resolved before discharge), with instructions to follow up with Neurology.

49 yo Female had a vasovagal syncope likely associated anxiety.  Patient received her 1st Moderna IM  dose at 12 n and was asked to to move to the next chair to allow her 19 yo son  to receive his vaccine.  While patient was watching son get vaccinated, she Felt dizzy and the vaccinator noted her closing her eyes, slowly lost tone, and fainted,  was guided to the floor preventing head trauma .  She was positioned supine with feet up . She did not appear pale, and opened her eyes within 5 minutes of Fainting , looked for her son, oriented to place and person. No focal weakness or deficits.  Initial vital signs showed mild hypotension 86/50 mmHg ( MAnual BP) , HR 99/min SpO2 98%, RR18/min not in distress but had shallow breathing.  After 5 minutes repeat BP was 100/70mmHg, HR mid to high 80?s , RR 18-20/min , improved tidal volume , able to take deeper breaths, not in respiratory distress .  Distal extremities warm and well perfumes  She was moved to a Gurney, HOB  45 degrees.  BP eventually increased to 140?s to 70? mmHg ( highest was 147/77 mmHg.  Sp02 consistently stable 98-98% on room air , HR high 80?s/min. She had no stridor , appeared comfortable , with clear speech , chest  clear breath sounds to auscultation, Heart RR,no murmur , good and equal radial and dorsal is pedis pulses.  Distal extremities warm and well perfused.   She  was kept under close observation until full recovery. She was able to sit up, allowed to rest , able to stand up, observed to have normal gait , was escorted to her car with no further incident.  Follow up phone call done 7 hours after the incident , she answered her cell phone, normal voice tone without stridor and verbalized she is feeling better , no recurrence of symptoms , no focal weakness. She has no primary care provider.  She was encouraged to find a primary care provider to monitor her BP and for health supervision. She verbalized understanding .
LAB_DATA: None exceptVS with pulse oximetry and BP noted above.

Signs of vertigo, mostly unsteadiness and having to walk with cane, and some vision impairment and inability to focus continued at least seven weeks, just recently having finally cleared. However, following three intratympanic injections of Prednisone, I still have total hearing loss in the right ear.

My 16 year old daughter had a "medical reaction" to the first Pfizer vaccine. The shot itself was fine. As we pulled away from the tent, in an alarmed voice, my daughter exclaimed that she could feel the shot traveling down her left arm into her hand. She said her arm felt really weird and her hand felt buzzy. By the time we rounded the corner to get to our mandatory 15 minute wait period, the reaction began. She lost eyesight and hearing - foggy hearing and began to sweat profusely. Her pupils were completely dilated. She became very weak and her hands were cold and clammy to the touch. The sweat was beading on her face and arms. Her hands became rigid and she cried that she can't move her fingers. When the ambulance arrived, they put her on oxygen - as she was blue at the extremities.  Her eyesight faded in and out several times throughout the reaction as did the foggy to almost gone hearing. We went to the hospital via ambulance. They tested her with an EKG. We were there for 4 hours. Her eyesight returned and her hearing became less foggy as time went on. When we left the hospital, my daughter was still very shaky. Her symptoms of shakiness lasted another 2-3 days and emotionally took another week to calm down. The trauma of the event is still with her. She was diagnosed with "medical reaction" from hospital.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I started to feel injection site pain and a headache approximately 4 hours after the injection. I then went to bed. I woke up at 5 AM and couldn't get back to sleep. I had an extremely severe headache. shaking chills, fever (fluctuated between 101 and 102) and severe fatigue and muscle and joint pain. Muscle and joint pain was primarily in my neck, shoulders, back and chest. It hurt to open my eyes or even move. I had no appetite and wasn't eating or drinking, but I urinated a lot, so I knew I was getting dehydrated. I tried to drink sips of water and managed to keep it down, until 11 PM on the day following the shot, I vomited and became nauseated. I had a hard time sleeping again. I woke up on the second day after the shot with a lingering headache and fatigue, but my fever was gone and I could move more easily. I gradually improved throughout the day. It doesn't sound terrible as I'm reading/writing this, but for about 36 hours; I haven't been that sick since I was a child, I don't think. It made me not want to have a booster shot if it's needed later. If I have to; I'll definitely need to have it on a Friday. I'm so jealous of people who've said they had no side effects or very mild ones. I had to take two days off work. I have to say though that although the side effects were severe and came on fairly quickly; they were also nearly all gone 48 hours after the shot. I felt so awful, it seemed like longer than 36 hours of misery, but in reality it wasn't.
HISTORY: High cholesterol, moderate obstructive sleep apnea and resulting chronic fatigue

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I recv'd Pfizer 4/28/21 @ 2pm in my right arm.  I signed up for 'V-Safe,' answered my questions for the 5-6days every afternoon, but on day 7 I had very odd symptoms.  Vaccine site began to hurt, is warm, swollen & itchy, but what hurts the most is my neck, and my Right Lymph node is painful, swollen & hard,  But I was no longer able to report.  I also have headaches related to the Right neck pain.

First night 5/4 exhaustion and headache.  Following morning 5/5 exhaustion, headache, pain/lump at injection site. All over muscle and joint pain. By late afternoon fever of 100.3. 5/6 lingering exhaustion. Temp went back to normal early morning hours. Injection site lump with redness, pain, hot to the touch growing. 5/7 Injection site pain, redness, hot to the touch have spread farther along upper arm.  Pain not muscle soreness, feels more like a deep painful bruise. All other symptoms have subsided.
ALLERGIES: Penicillins Class Sulfa (Sulfonamide Antibiotics) Minocycline Sumatriptan Succinate Venlafaxine

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Shingles infection. Blisters first appeared May 7 on my left shoulder.

My husband was the one who was vaccinated by the Pfizer vaccine. I am currently nursing our 16 month old and had not had a period since I became Pregnant with her. One week after my husband received his second vaccine my period is back! I attribute this to the vaccine.

Mild fever <100�, mild chills, severe exhaustion, severe body aches, fogginess. This lasted about 36 hours, with the exception of the left hand. The left hand experienced carpal tunnel and arthritis-like symptoms for 6 days longer than all other symptoms. It then went away on its own. To my knowledge, I hadn?t in any way performed stressful or repetitive behaviors leading up to the symptoms; I had been bedridden with the vaccine side-effects and was too exhausted to do much of anything.

heightened reflux like symptoms; belching; spitting up; fussiness; fever as well around 100 degrees Fahrenheit; This spontaneous report was received from a physician and refers to a 2-month-old male patient.  The patient's concurrent conditions  included being fussy and colic like with belching and spitting up (all started since birth). The patient's mother had cut out dairy to help with these symptoms, and it was helping. His medical history was reported as none, concomitant medications were not reported.   On 09-APR-2021, the patient was vaccinated with rotavirus vaccine, live, oral, pentavalent (ROTATEQ), 2 milliliter, (lot # 1742457, expiration date reported as 16-JAN-2022, but upon internal validation established as 06-JAN-2022), administered orally for prevention of rotavirus. On the same day, he was vaccinated with  hib conj vaccine (tet toxoid), diphtheria toxoid, pertussis acellular 5-component vaccine, poliovirus vaccine inactivated (mrc-5), tetanus toxoid (PENTACEL) (strength, dose, route of administration, lot number, expiry date and indication were not reported) and with pneumococcal 13v conj vaccine (crm197) (PREVNAR 13) (strength, dose, route of administration, lot number, expiry date and indication were not reported).  On the same day, the patient experienced heightened reflux like symptoms, he was worse again with fussiness (severe), belching and spitting up. He had a fever as well around 100 degrees Fahrenheit for one day after the vaccine. The mother was feeling like he was back to or worse than before he had the vaccine. The patient sought medical attention. No treatment was administered due to the events and no laboratory diagnostics was performed. The outcome of the events was not reported.  The causal relationship between the events and the suspect vaccines was unknown. Since the patient received all suspect vaccines on the same day, the physician was not sure which vaccine or vaccines caused side effects.
CUR_ILL: Burping (since birth); Dairy free diet; Infantile colic (since birth); Infantile spitting up (since birth); Irritability (since birth)

Pneumonia; chronic coughing; wheezing; Information has been received from a lawyer referring to a female patient of unknown age regarding a case in litigation. Information about concurrent condition, history condition and concomitant medication was not reported. On or about 03-JUL-2017, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) (strength, dose, route, lot# and expiration date unknown) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). Shortly after receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered pneumonia and subsequent chronic coughing and wheezing. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms have resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the vaccine. The patient also experiences mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient has suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events pneumonia and subsequent chronic coughing and wheezing was considered to be not recovered and causal relationship was assessed as related.    The lawyer considered the event pneumonia and subsequent chronic coughing and wheezing to be disability.   Upon internal review, pneumonia was determined to be medically significant.

postherpetic neuralgia; scleroderma; herpes zoster; Information has been received regarding a case in litigation from a lawyer and referred to a female patient of unknown age. No information was provided regarding medical history, concurrent conditions, or concomitant medications. On or around 30-MAR-2017, the patient was vaccinated with zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) for routine health maintenance and for its intended purpose: the prevention of shingles (herpes zoster). After receiving zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered herpes zoster, postherpetic neuralgia, scleroderma and Raynaud's disease. As a result of these symptoms, the patient was seen and treated by her medical providers and was still under their care. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient's symptoms had resulted in physical limitations not present prior to using the product. The patient also experienced mental and emotional distress due to resulting physical limitations and seriousness of her condition. As a result of the manufacturer, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries, as well as significant conscious pain and suffering, mental anguish, emotional distress, loss of enjoyment of life, physical impairment and injury. As a direct and proximate result of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX), the patient had suffered and incurred damages, including medical expenses; the loss of accumulations; and other economic and non-economic damages. The outcome of the events herpes zoster, postherpetic neuralgia and scleroderma was considered as not recovered. The causality assessment between the events herpes zoster, postherpetic neuralgia, scleroderma and zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) was considered as related by the lawyer.    The lawyer considered the events herpes zoster, postherpetic neuralgia and scleroderma to be disability. Upon internal review, scleroderma was determined to be medically significant.

She was found to have contracted HPV; Losing 1 to 2 pounds in the last several years; She is sad, confused and shocked; She is sad, confused and shocked; She is sad, confused and shocked; Cervical Cancer stage 0 / PAP smear-irregularities; I got HPV 18 despite getting the GARDAIL and GARDASIL9 / The vaccine she received did not protect her from contracting the strain of HPV.; Diagnosed with HPV 18; Received 1 dose of GARDASIL and then received the "Improved version of GARDASIL" which was GARDASIL9; This spontaneous report was received from an approximately 18-year-old non-pregnant female patient regarding herself.  The patient was not sexually active, no information was provided regarding the patient's medical history, drug reactions, allergies or concomitant medications.  On an unknown date, when the patient was a child, the patient was vaccinated with Quadrivalent Human Papillomavirus (Types 6,11,16,18) Recomb. Vaccine (GARDASIL) for prophylaxis (strength, dose number, anatomical location, route of administration, lot number and expiration date were not reported).  On an unspecified date in 2012,  reported as  2012 or 2013, she was starting school , the patient was vaccinated with HPV rL1 6 11 16 18 31 33 45 52 58 VLP vaccine (yeast) (GARDASIL 9) for prophylaxis (strength, dose number, anatomical location, route of administration, lot number and expiration date were not reported). The vaccine was administered by her mother that was a Obstetrician and Gynecologyst.   Since an unknown date, reported as "in the last several years", the patient had been losing 1 to 2 pounds (weight decreased).   On an unknown date, reported as about couple years ago, irregularities were found on her papanicolaou (PAP) smear and she was found to have contracted human papilloma virus (HPV) (HPV infection) exact strain unknown at the time.  On an unspecified date in 2020, the patient her PAP came back with irregularities again. On 03-SEP-2020, she had a loop electrosurgical excision procedure (LEEP) and was diagnosed with HPV 18. On 20-OCT-2020, she received colposcopy of cervix and diagnosed with stage 0 cervical cancer (cervix carcinoma stage 0). On 29-JAN-2021, the pre-cancerous cells were removed.   The patient stated that the vaccines that she received did not protect her from contracting the strain of HPV she should have been protected from, she got HPV 18 despite getting the vaccines (vaccination failure). Since an unknown date, the patient was sad (depressed mood), confused (confusional state) and shocked (also reported as disturbed) (feeling abnormal) because she somehow managed to get the HPV strain despite getting the vaccine.  The outcome of the events weight decreased, depressed mood, confusional state and feeling abnormal was reported as not resolved and for the remaining events was not reported. The causal relationship between the event vaccination failure and vaccination with quadrivalent Human Papillomavirus (Types 6,11,16,18) Recomb. Vaccine (GARDASIL) and HPV rL1 6 11 16 18 31 33 45 52 58 VLP vaccine (yeast) (GARDASIL 9) was assessed as related but for the remaining events the causal relationship was unknown.  Upon internal review, the event cervix carcinoma stage 0 was considered to be medically significant.

30 minutes of rapid heart rate and fluttering; shortness of breath; supraventricular tachycardia; Dizzy; diaphoretic; Palpitations; Fatigue; nauseous; This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of CARDIAC FLUTTER (30 minutes of rapid heart rate and fluttering) in a 77-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 025J20-2A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     No Medical History information was reported.    On 21-Dec-2020, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 21-Dec-2020, the patient experienced CARDIAC FLUTTER (30 minutes of rapid heart rate and fluttering) (seriousness criterion medically significant), DYSPNOEA (shortness of breath), SUPRAVENTRICULAR TACHYCARDIA (supraventricular tachycardia), DIZZINESS (Dizzy), HYPERHIDROSIS (diaphoretic), PALPITATIONS (Palpitations), FATIGUE (Fatigue) and NAUSEA (nauseous). On 21-Dec-2020, CARDIAC FLUTTER (30 minutes of rapid heart rate and fluttering) had resolved. At the time of the report, DYSPNOEA (shortness of breath), SUPRAVENTRICULAR TACHYCARDIA (supraventricular tachycardia), DIZZINESS (Dizzy), HYPERHIDROSIS (diaphoretic), PALPITATIONS (Palpitations), FATIGUE (Fatigue) and NAUSEA (nauseous) outcome was unknown.      DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 21-Dec-2020, Electrocardiogram: abnormal (abnormal) supraventricular tachycardia. On 21-Dec-2020, Heart rate: increased (High) increased.     The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   No relevant concomitant medications were provided. About 3 hours after receiving vaccine, patient had 30 minutes of rapid heart rate, and fluttering. She laid down, went to sleep, and it resolved. She didn't seek emergency care. Did not have chest pain or shortness of breath.  Continued to have palpitations occasionally, fatigue, tachycardia. She presented to primary care professional on 07 Jan 2021 for symptoms and was transferred to for additional cardiac workup and treatment after capturing supraventricular tachycardia (SVT) on electrocardiogram (EKG). Also diaphoretic, dizzy, nauseous, shortness of breath with palpitations. She was given IV metoprolol in ED with conversion to normal sinus rhythm (NSR). They suspect that the vaccine may have been her trigger. She was able to discharge without escalation of care.  Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Amnesia; Cardiac disorder; Thrombosis; Transient ischaemic attack; This case was received via another Manufacturer (Reference number: vsafe) on 27-Apr-2021 and was forwarded to Moderna on 27-Apr-2021.    This regulatory authority case was reported by an other health care professional and describes the occurrence of AMNESIA (Amnesia), CARDIAC DISORDER (Cardiac disorder), THROMBOSIS (Thrombosis) and TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischaemic attack) in a 70-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 027L20A) for COVID-19 vaccination.     The patient's past medical history included Glaucoma and Hypothyroidism. Concurrent medical conditions included Stroke. Concomitant products included LEVOTHYROXINE, BRIMONIDINE, LATANOPROST and TIMOLOL for an unknown indication.    On 13-Jan-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 14-Jan-2021, the patient experienced AMNESIA (Amnesia) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), CARDIAC DISORDER (Cardiac disorder) (seriousness criterion hospitalization), THROMBOSIS (Thrombosis) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant) and TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischaemic attack) (seriousness criteria hospitalization and medically significant). At the time of the report, AMNESIA (Amnesia), CARDIAC DISORDER (Cardiac disorder), THROMBOSIS (Thrombosis) and TRANSIENT ISCHAEMIC ATTACK (Transient ischaemic attack) had resolved.      DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 14-Jan-2021, Catheterisation cardiac: inconclusive. On 14-Jan-2021, Echocardiogram: inconclusive. On 14-Jan-2021, Magnetic resonance imaging: inconclusive. On 14-Jan-2021, Ultrasound scan: inconclusive.     The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown.   For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments.   The next day, the patient had short term memory loss, patient went to the hospital, and they said patient had some type of heart episode. The patient was taken by ambulance to the hospital and was told  had a blood clot in brain and had suffered a mini stroke. The patient was hospitalized for 4 nights. The patient was given blood thinner and got improved.  Company comment: Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 vaccine, the onset of the reported events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.  However patient had an underlying risk in the past history of stroke.; Sender's Comments: Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association between the use of mRNA-1273 vaccine, the onset of the reported events, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Low fill of 2 Shingrix vials after reconstitution/ only able to withdraw 0.3 mL /swabbed the top of the adjuvant / withdraw 0.5 mL of liquid / able to withdraw only 0.3 mL total solution / unsure if the adjuvant or antigen are the affected component; withdraw only 0.3 mL total solution / administered to a patient / notified the patient of the low fill of the dose; only able to withdraw 0.3 mL after reconstitution; This case was reported by a pharmacist and described the occurrence of underdose in a 73-year-old female patient who received Herpes zoster (Shingrix) (batch number 9472F, expiry date 14th October 2022) and (batch number MM59F, expiry date 14th October 2022) for prophylaxis. This case was associated with a product complaint.   Co-suspect products included Herpes zoster (Shingrix) (batch number 9472F, expiry date 14th October 2022) and (batch number MM59F, expiry date 14th October 2022) for prophylaxis.   On 29th April 2021, the patient received Shingrix (intramuscular). On an unknown date, the dose was an unknown dose. On 29th April 2021, the patient received Shingrix (intramuscular). On an unknown date, the dose was an unknown dose. On 29th April 2021, unknown after receiving Shingrix and not applicable after receiving Shingrix, the patient experienced underdose and package volume underfill. On an unknown date, the patient experienced pharmaceutical product complaint. On an unknown date, the outcome of the underdose, package volume underfill and pharmaceutical product complaint were unknown.  Additional details were provided as follows: The patient herself was the reporter. She reported low fill of two Shingrix vials after reconstitution.  Both vials came out of the same box and the total reconstituted volume was between 0.3 and 0.4 mL for both.  When preparing the first injection, the reporter swabbed the top of the adjuvant vial and injected 0.5mL of air into the vial. She then withdrew 0.5 mL of liquid. She swabbed the top of the antigen vial, then inserted the liquid adjuvant and was only able to withdraw 0.3 mL. This dose was not administered and was discarded. There was no patient involvement.  With the second vial, the pharmacist swabbed the top of the adjuvant and did not inject air into the vial. She was able to withdraw 0.5 mL of liquid. She swabbed the top of the antigen, inserted the needle to reconstitute and was able to withdraw only 0.3 mL total solution. This dose was administered to the patient which led to underdose and package volume underfill. The pharmacist notified the patient of the low fill of the dose.  No resulting patient symptoms were noted.  The reporter was unsure if the adjuvant or antigen were the affected component. A picture of the defect product was taken and emailed.  Suspect product was not available for return as it had been discarded.  It was unknown if other vials in that particular box were affected.  The vial after reconstitution were swirled laterally for about 15 seconds, it was held upside-down when the vaccine was being withdrawn.  The reporter was able to withdraw between 0.3 and 0.4 mL for both vials and 3 ml syringe was used with 0.1 ml interval hash marks. The reporter had not experienced a low fill problem with this product before. No leaks or cracks were observed in vial. The reporter consented to follow up via email.

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     The patient's past medical history included Colitis (Have not been taking medications from 3-4 years). Concurrent medical conditions included Hypertension, Diabetes, Cholesterol high and Drug allergy (Allergic to NSAIDS). Concomitant products included HYDROCHLOROTHIAZIDE, LISINOPRIL (LISINOPRIL HCTZ) for Blood pressure high, METFORMIN for Diabetes, ATORVASTATIN for High cholesterol, ACETYLSALICYLIC ACID (BABY ASPIRIN) and MINERALS NOS, VITAMINS NOS (ONE A DAY ADVANCE ADULTS) for an unknown indication. On 18-Feb-2021, the patient experienced VACCINATION SITE PAIN (sharp pain at the injection site), HEADACHE (severe headache), PYREXIA (100-103 degree temperature), ARTHRALGIA (joint pain) and MYALGIA (muscle aches). On 20-Feb-2021, the patient experienced CHILLS (bad chills). On 04-Mar-2021, the patient experienced GAIT DISTURBANCE (severe body ache unable to walk or move without assistance). On 06-Mar-2021, the patient experienced RENAL FAILURE (Kidney failure) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and DIALYSIS (emergency dialysis) (seriousness criterion hospitalization). Her temps ranged from 97.5-98.7 on 04Feb2021. She experienced fatigue. She did not know the seriousness for any of the side effects she experienced. As of 05Feb2021, her headache has improved. She was still experiencing sleepiness and fatigue. The chills she developed mid day. She had not them right now. She has better and worse moments just like when she had COVID. She was worried about the second one. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included body temperature: 97.5-98.7 on 04Feb2021, COVID-19: positive in Dec2020. No other relevant tests. Patient stated that born with the disability in her right hand and a cyst, they just didn't find the cyst until she was 39 and that's when she had the surgery. Family history was reported as none. The patient historical vaccine included first dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 mRNA VACCINE; Lot number: EL1283, Expiry date: 30Apr2021) on 17Jan2021 for COVID-19 immunisation. Now she was still having pain in that arm, but it's not exactly where the shot was, it's running down her arm and it's not constant, it comes and goes. States that she did have rotator cuff surgery in 2013, and that's kind of what the pain feels like now. States that yesterday her arm didn't feel as bad as it does today. It's more aggravating. Again, states that the pain was like what she had after her rotator cuff surgery. States that she hasn't felt that pain since her surgery, then on Sunday when she got the shot the pain has kind of started back up. States that it has definitely improved. On Monday and Tuesday, she would feel a little twinge of pain about every 3-4 hours, but today it's every 10-15 minutes. The patient not visited emergency room and not visited physician office. The outcome of the event pain in left arm was recovering and was unknown for another event.

A patient of unspecified age and gender received second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), via an unspecified route of administration on 11Mar2021 (Lot Number: EB6204, unknown expiration) as a single dose for COVID-19 immunisation.  The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported. The patient received first dose of BNT162B2 on 18Feb2021 (Lot: EN6201, unknown expiration) for COVID-19 immunization and experienced sore arm. Upon receiving the second dosage on 11Mar2021, the patient was extremely tired for about 10 days in Mar2021. The two-week period after vaccination was 25Mar2021. On 28Mar2021, the patient had an episode of gout. The patient had to go to the hospital because the patient could not walk. The patient was diagnosed with gout and given medication which took care of it. The patient had never had any episodes of gout, so it was a surprise to the patient that suddenly would have an episode of gout. Since then on 13Apr2021, the patient has seen the primary care doctor. The patient had urine and blood test and the numbers were normal on unspecified dates. The patient was asked if this could have been a reaction to the vaccine. The patient recovered from extreme fatigue on unspecified date in Mar2021. Outcome of the remaining events was unknown. The events could not walk, and gout were assessed as serious (hospitalization). The event fatigue was assessed as non-serious.  No follow-up attempts are possible. No further information is expected.

I had covid late Jan of this year. The vaccine more interaction due to that if I had immunity to it. It was so bad I don't know if it's possible to wait 2 months for the 2nd shot. I heard the first dose 80-90 percent immunity or even more. With my body I never had this reaction. Today I'm a whole lot better (day 6). I am too putting too much, should I wait 90 days other say 4 weeks. What to do about the 2nd dose? How about using antihistamines during/after my second dose? What about Tylenol or Ibuprofen?"  I had a side effect after the first dose of the vaccine.  Should I get the second dose?  e-transmitting potential duplicate AE. Caller said he didn't give PCP information to the safety agent. He did not have. Response: Spoke from EUA PI (Revised: 06 April 2021) under Post Authorization Experience Fact Sheet for Recipients and Caregivers (Revised: 06 April 2021) under section WHAT ARE THE RISKS OF THE PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE? As noted in the Fact Sheet for Recipients, you should not get the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine if you had a severe allergic reaction after a previous dose of the vaccine or if you had a severe allergic reaction to any ingredient of the vaccine. The decision to receive the second dose for any other reason cannot be made by Pfizer. We refer you to speak to your healthcare provider about the risks of the vaccine compared to the risks of potentially not being fully protected against COVID-19 infection. Your healthcare provider knows your health situation and has access to information that can better help inform this decision. A 23-year-old female patient received the second dose of BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, solution for injection), via an unspecified route of administration, administered in right arm on 21Apr2021 08:45 (Batch/Lot number was not reported) (at the age of 23 years old) as single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient medical history was not reported. The patient was not pregnant at the time of vaccination. Concomitant medication included ibuprofen. The patient previously took septra and experienced allergies (known allergies); and first dose of BNT162B2 on 31Mar2021 08:45 at right arm for COVID-19 immunization. No other vaccine in four weeks. On 22Apr2021, the patient had a fever of up to 103.5 and was down to around 102 by the time of the incident (around 4:00). The patient woke up and was standing for about 3 minutes to refill water when she got super nauseous. She was making her way to the bathroom to throw up, and the next thing she knew she was on the floor. The patient was not sure how long she was passed out for though she had no reason to believe it was long. She tried to sit up, but she really wasn't feeling well, so she laid back down and closed her eyes for a bit. Then she got super hot and sweaty. Once that passed (maybe a few more minutes), she was able to check her temperature and she was down to around 101 and was able to get back to bed. No treatment for the events. No COVID prior vaccination. The patient had not been COVID tested post vaccination. The outcome of the events was recovered in Apr2021.   Information about Batch/Lot number has been requested.

The patient experienced what scared her was not feeling like she was getting enough oxygen on an unspecified date, problems breathing/her breathing still almost feels labored on 11Apr2021, arm hurt on 09Apr2021, pain in her back where her lungs are on 11Apr2021, hot and cold sweats on 10Apr2021, dizzy on 10Apr2021, shaky on 10Apr2021, nausea on 13Apr2021, body pain/flu-like body pain in her muscles over her shoulders on 11Apr2021, out of it on 11Apr2021, weak on 10Apr2021, tired on 10Apr2021, headache on 10Apr2021, anxious on 10Apr2021, fever on 10Apr2021, itchy on 09Apr2021, feeling like maybe there is something wrong with her spleen on an unspecified date, the pain is in the left side of the back kind of by the lungs on an unspecified date, she has been sick on an unspecified date, her mental status was also affected on an unspecified date. Patient had the first dose of the Covid Vaccine on 09Apr2021 and gradually her arm hurt, she had hot sweats, she felt dizzy, was shaky, had nausea, and had body pain. The one thing she is concerned about was she had pain in her back where her lungs are and she was having problems breathing. She has a little bit of that still. She has also been out of it. Her breathing still almost feels labored, and this past weekend she thought she would go to the emergency room. Her main concern is this awful pain in her back while she was having problems breathing and getting enough oxygen. She felt weak, dizzy, and shaky. She got scared. She has been sick, she had cancer a long time ago. What scared her was not feeling like she was getting enough oxygen. The pain is in the left side of the back kind of by the lungs. It goes directly from the front to the back. On Monday it started feeling better. Today it is so much better. She will feel like she is not getting enough oxygen or giving a full breath and then this in her back. She remembers having pneumonia years ago and having pain in her lungs. That's why she knows the pain is in the back of her lungs. She has to say she is a smoker. She slowed down and couldn't smoke this week or during that. She kind of quit, that's her reality now. The pain comes and goes throughout the day but it is not as bad. She didn't have this shortness of breath and other things until a couple days after she got the vaccine. It gradually came up on her. She was not having trouble breathing, it was more slightly labored. It was not profound, just there. Sometimes when she is speaking after a while she gets tired and will have to take a moment and take a deep breath. It is so much better. She called her primary care physician and was anxious, and all he said was she would feel effects for 2 weeks. He wasn't very helpful. Her arm hurt the day that she had the shot. Even today there are little bits of pain but very light. 09Apr2021 through 11Apr2021 was when everything really hit. It was hard to lift up her arm. It was a little pain, it was no big deal. She would have the AC on and blast it when she had the hot and cold sweats. She was using napkins because she was sweating profusely. It felt like she obviously had a reaction to the vaccine. It's normal she guesses. She didn't expect it for the first dose. The 11th, 12th, 13th, and 14th it was really bad. Her whole body was sweating and would get wet. She'd be hot and then cold. She was anxious because she was having problems breathing. She still gets a little bit of hot and cold sweats, but nothing compared to what she went through. As the days go on she is slowly getting better. She was dizzy not just during the day, at night she couldn't sleep because of it. She has gradually gotten better. Yesterday she tried to do some gardening but felt so weak she had to come back inside. When she gets up she feels weak and a little bit of lack of air. She has labored breathing. She was real itchy. The shakiness, dizziness, and anxiety all came on and were horrible. She doesn't know if the nausea was because she couldn't eat and had to take her regular medication. It was very light nausea. She had flu-like body pain in her muscles over her shoulders. Her headache was major too during all of this. The headache is something that comes and goes still. It is a weird kind of headache. She had a fever and got like flu all over body pain. She doesn't know how to explain how she felt out of it. She doesn't know if it was the fact she was so sick. She had a feeling of did she do that. She couldn't make decisions. She would need to take the garbage out and go back to the garbage and think what did she come here for. Her mental status was also affected. The weakness gradually got really bad, and she still hasn't recovered from it. She still feels weak and tired when trying to do things. She was tired the day after she got the vaccine. The first day she thought it was nothing and she was fine. Gradually it got real bad when she was sick. She didn't feel that flu-ish feeling but was weak and tired. She got dizzy and she had the brain fog thing. She was having really bad headaches during the same time. The weakness and tiredness go hand in hand. She takes a mineral for her thoracic spine, but she takes that more for elderly arthritis. She doesn't have any conditions that she thinks played a role. She has been feeling like maybe there is something wrong with her spleen. Took Tylenol for her fever. Mentioned fever would go away and come back. The patient underwent lab tests and procedures which included body temperature: 102, 99 and 100.1 (unit unspecified) all on unspecified dates.  Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of fever and itchy. Outcome of the event problems breathing/her breathing still almost feels labored, arm hurt, pain in her back where her lungs are, hot and cold sweats, dizzy, out of it and headache was recovering. Outcome of the event fever was recovered on 13Apr2021, itchy was recovered with sequelae on 14Apr2021, body pain/flu-like body pain in her muscles over her shoulders was recovered on 16Apr2021, nausea was recovered on 16Apr2021, shaky was recovered on 19Apr2021. Outcome of the event weak and tired was not recovered. Outcome of all the other events was unknown.

Many pregnant persons are receiving messenger RNA (mRNA) coronavirus disease 2019 (Covid-19) vaccines, but data are limited on their safety in pregnancy. Method: From 14Dec2020, to 28Feb2021, authors used data from the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS), and other data to characterize the initial safety of mRNA Covid-19 vaccines in pregnant persons. Result: A total of 35,691 participants 16 to 54 years of age identified as pregnant. Injection-site pain was reported more frequently among pregnant persons than among nonpregnant women, whereas headache, myalgia, chills, and fever were reported less frequently. Among 3958 participants enrolled 827 had a completed pregnancy, of which 115 (13.9%) resulted in a pregnancy loss and 712 (86.1%) resulted in a live birth (mostly among participants with vaccination in the third trimester). Adverse neonatal outcomes included preterm birth (in 9.4%) and small size for gestational age (in 3.2%); no neonatal deaths were reported. Although not directly comparable, calculated proportions of adverse pregnancy and neonatal outcomes in persons vaccinated against Covid-19 who had a completed pregnancy were similar to incidences reported in studies involving pregnant women that were conducted before the Covid-19 pandemic. Among 221 pregnancy-related adverse events reported to the VAERS, the most frequently reported event was spontaneous abortion (46 cases). Conclusions: Preliminary findings did not show obvious safety signals among pregnant persons who received mRNA Covid-19 vaccines. However, more longitudinal follow-up, including follow-up of large numbers of women vaccinated earlier in pregnancy, is necessary to inform maternal, pregnancy, and infant outcomes. The patient travelled and got infected with covid and died yesterday (02May2021). The reporter stated that it looked like the vaccine might not be as effective with the new variants. After two Pfizer vaccines shots , this doctor travelled to see his parents and succumbed to the new variant. Outcome of the event was fatal.  No follow up attempts are possible; Information about Lot and batch number could not be obtained. No further information is expected.; Reported Cause(s) of Death: got infected with covid and died yesterday.

Anaphylaxis After the Covid-19 Vaccine; This is a literature report.   Authors reported a case of the first patient at the (Hospital), who had immediate anaphylaxis after administration of the Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine. Authors highlighted that the patient never had an episode of anaphylaxis previously and had nonreactive skin testing for polyethylene glycol, polysorbatecontaining vaccines, as well as the Covid-19 vaccine itself. Importantly, she had an underlying condition that predisposed her to non-IgE-mediated anaphylaxis. The case is a 34-year-old female healthcare professional, who presented to the Allergy and Immunology clinic for evaluation of an anaphylaxis event that occurred after administration of the first dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine. The patient had negative SARS-CoV-2 nucleic acid tests 109 and 39 days before immunization. She noted in the interview to have been subjectively overheated while standing in line waiting to receive the first dose of the vaccine. Within 3 min of vaccine administration, she developed flushing, urticaria on her extremities and face, generalized pruritus, tongue swelling, nausea, light-headedness, racing pulse, and shortness of breath with absence of wheezing. Emergency medical personnel responded and administered intramuscular epinephrine and diphenhydramine. She noted substantial relief within minutes of administration of these medicines. The patient was transported to the emergency department for monitoring and had no further reaction. After discharge, she noted erythema and hives around the site of injection, which were nearly resolved by the time of our evaluation 2 days later. Two years earlier, she noted a large hive at the site of injection that took days to resolve after receiving preservative free quadrivalent influenza vaccine, Fluarix (GlaxoSmithKline) without associated systemic symptoms. Two months before the anaphylaxis event, she received Afluria (Seqirus), quadrivalent preservative-free influenza vaccine. Again, she noted a large local hive at the site of injection without a systemic reaction. She also described a history of childhood asthma and eczema but had never had an episode of anaphylaxis. She lastly described a greater than 10-year history of inducible episodes of pruritus, swelling, and hives that were most notable at times of sweating. She noted an inability to take warm showers as well as limitations with exercise due to pruritus and hives in what was suspicious for cholinergic urticaria. Authors performed an examination, laboratory studies, and several procedures for evaluating her anaphylaxis episode. Laboratory evaluation showed elevation in C-reactive protein (CRP) (1.27 mg/dL) 2 days following immunization, negative chronic urticaria (CU) index (4.3), and IgE levels (74.98 IU/mL) within the reference range. Dermatographism was not present. Skin examination revealed no skin findings of cutaneous mastocytosis. Serum tryptase was 4.7 ug/L and 5.4 ug/L checked 7 and 26 days, respectively, after the event and was within reference range; tryptase was not checked before or during the event. The tryptase alpha/beta 1 (TPSAB1) copy number variation test did not reveal tandem duplication(s) of TPSAB1 by allele-specific PCR. Prick puncture skin testing for polyethylene glycol, Prevnar 23 (Merck), and Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 (Pfizer) was negative. She scored 11 of 21 on the cholinergic urticaria disease severity standardized scale, suggesting moderate level of the disease. Authors further confirmed cholinergic urticaria via exercise provocation challenge guided by a standardized protocol. Based on the history and findings, her systemic reaction after receiving the Covid-19 vaccine was most consistent with anaphylaxis from a severe episode of cholinergic urticaria. Cholinergic urticaria has a known association with anaphylaxis although most people usually have only cutaneous symptoms. Because of her newly diagnosed cholinergic urticaria and recent anaphylaxis episode, authors recommended she carry an epinephrine auto-injector. Authors also recommended non-sedating antihistamine therapy for prevention of urticaria during bathing and exercise once she was done breastfeeding. Lastly, authors recommended all vaccines including the second dose of the Covid-19 vaccine be administered under supervision in a cool room without excessive clothing. The protection data after a single dose of the vaccine was unclear at the time so administering a single dose was not considered ideal. Based on the evaluation and the patient's increased risk for SARS-CoV-2 exposure, she, after informed decision making, accepted a second dose of the Pfizer-BioNTech Covid-19 vaccine. Authors recommended against pre-medications since they were able perform the challenge in a cool room and confirm that she was not sweating or overheating. Authors also did not want to mask an IgE-mediated reaction in the event of false-negative skin testing. In addition, the patient did not want to use any antihistamines as her infant was not weaned and still breastfeeding. She tolerated her second dose, without premedication, exhibiting only transient, mild nausea and a sense of warmth, but without any objective findings. Vaccines have an overall excellent safety profile; this includes data from Covid-19 vaccine clinical trials. Authors highlighted that the patient showed propensity for allergic reactions even before administration of the Covid-19 vaccine based on her localized reaction to the influenza vaccines and her history of cholinergic urticaria. It was important for them to evaluate whether IgE-mediated anaphylaxis might underlie her case. Authors showed that the patient had nonreactive skin testing with both 1:1 epicutaneous and 1:100 and 1:10 intradermal Covid-19 vaccine and drugs containing polysorbate 80. However, more data are needed to determine skin testing's role in predicting IgE-mediated Covid-19 vaccine allergy. Likewise, evaluation of mast cell activation in addition to IgE-mediated allergy needs to be considered after any episode of anaphylaxis or potentially severe cutaneous reaction to Covid-19 vaccinations. Evaluations should include the evaluation of inducible urticaria disorders, hereditary alpha tryptasemia, mastocytosis, and idiopathic mast cell activation disorders. Assuming that immediate Covid-19 vaccine reactions correlate to an IgE-mediated allergy ignores other non-contraindicating etiologies and potentially erroneously denies patients the benefit of immunization. Thus, the general public should be aware of immune conditions that may place a person at risk of anaphylaxis, but that these may not be specific to the Covid-19 vaccine. Distinctly, CDC guidance notes "If you had an immediate allergic reaction after getting a shot of a Covid-19 vaccine, you should not get a second shot of that vaccine, even if your allergic reaction was not severe enough to require emergency care." The fact that the patient with a common mast cell disorder was able to safely receive the second dose of the Covid-19 vaccine following anaphylaxis suggests that anaphylaxis may not represent an absolute contraindication but validates the recommendation that these cases should be evaluated by an allergist and an immunologist for directed care and not be categorically denied the Covid-19 vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Covid infection >14 days after first eligible dose of vaccination; Covid infection >14 days after first eligible dose of vaccination; This is a literature report. This literature report from a physician reporting same event under the same suspect product for 9 patients. This is one of 9 reports.  Many pregnant persons are receiving messenger RNA (mRNA) coronavirus disease 2019 (Covid-19) vaccines, but data are limited on their safety in pregnancy. Method: From 14Dec2020, to 28Feb2021, authors used data from the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS) and other data to characterize the initial safety of mRNA Covid-19 vaccines in pregnant persons. Result: A total of 35,691 participants 16 to 54 years of age identified as pregnant. Injection-site pain was reported more frequently among pregnant persons than among nonpregnant women, whereas headache, myalgia, chills, and fever were reported less frequently. Among 3958 participants enrolled, 827 had a completed pregnancy, of which 115 (13.9%) resulted in a pregnancy loss and 712 (86.1%) resulted in a live birth (mostly among participants with vaccination in the third trimester). Adverse neonatal outcomes included preterm birth (in 9.4%) and small size for gestational age (in 3.2%); no neonatal deaths were reported. Although not directly comparable, calculated proportions of adverse pregnancy and neonatal outcomes in persons vaccinated against Covid-19 who had a completed pregnancy were similar to incidences reported in studies involving pregnant women that were conducted before the Covid-19 pandemic. Among 221 pregnancy-related adverse events reported to the VAERS, the most frequently reported event was spontaneous abortion (46 cases). Conclusions: Preliminary findings did not show obvious safety signals among pregnant persons who received mRNA Covid-19 vaccines. However, more longitudinal follow-up, including follow-up of large numbers of women vaccinated earlier in pregnancy, is necessary to inform maternal, pregnancy, and infant outcomes.  An adult female patient received bnt162b2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE), first dose via an unspecified route of administration on an unspecified date at single dose for COVID-19 immunization. The patient's medical history and concomitant medications were not reported.  The patient experienced COVID infection more than 14 days after first eligible dose of vaccination on an unspecified date. The mother reported she became pregnant while taking bnt162b2.  The outcome of the event was unknown.  No follow-up attempts are needed. No further information is expected.; Sender's Comments: A causal association between BNT162B2 and the reported events cannot be excluded based on a compatible temporal relation. However, full immunity is only expected 7 days after the second dose.,Linked Report(s) : US-PFIZER INC-2021480902 Pfizer

A patient received an expired vaccine, no AE; Initial information regarding an unsolicited valid non-serious case was received from other healthcare professional via Medical Information (MI) (Reference number- 00567200) and transmitted to Sanofi on 19-Apr-2021.  This case involves a four-year-old female patient received an expired 0.5 mL 4th dose IPV (VERO) [IPOL] (lot R1B25 and expiry date: 13-Mar-2021) via an intramuscular route in the right thigh for prophylactic vaccination on 16-Apr-2021 (expired product administered).  The patient's medical history, past medical treatment(s), vaccination(s) and family history were not provided.  Concomitant medications included MEASLES VACCINE, MUMPS VACCINE, RUBELLA VACCINE (MMR) and DIPHTHERIA VACCINE TOXOID, PERTUSSIS VACCINE ACELLULAR, TETANUS VACCINE TOXOID (DTAP) for prophylactic vaccination.  This was a case of actual medication error case due to expired vaccine used (latency same day).  At the time of reporting, no adverse event was reported. Hello,  Had the 2nd Moderna COVID-19 vaccine at the pharmacy on April 2nd at 6:45 PM.  The nurse asked me to stay around the store for 15 minutes for any immediate side effects, and to drink plenty of water when I got home.  Did some shopping, and probably left about 30-45 minutes after the shot with no side-effects, and when I arrived home about another 45 minutes later still had no side effects.  Upon waking the next morning my right arm where I received the shot was extremely painful, and I could not raise any higher than parallel to the floor without extreme pain for 2-3 days.  Then I also started with a slight fever, which of the times checked, reached about 101.  Also was getting muscle and joint soreness, and later that started getting extreme cramping in my leg calf muscles while sitting on the couch.  I then had to stand up for 5-10 minutes, or walk around a little and then after sitting the extreme cramping would begin again so I would have to stand up again.  That went on all day.  When laying down that night the cramping would subside enough to sleep a little on and off during the night.  The calf muscle cramping started to gradually subside, but took about 17 days to go completely away.  The day after the vaccine when my legs were cramping I was extremely worried about possible leg clots since I had never had extreme leg cramping like that my entire life, and I was drinking plenty of water like the nurse recommended.  Best regards,

On the day of the vaccine, April 29, which I got in the morning, I experienced headache, malaise, pain in arm.  On the sixth day after the vaccine, May 5,  my left eyelid began to swell and continued to worsen each day.  The swelling was in the eyelid and above the eyelid.  The swelling was the most extreme first thing in the morning.  My eye itself was unaffected.  The swelling is extreme enough to interfere with vision and is noticeable to anyone looking at me from at least six feet away.  On the third day of swelling, I noticed that the area about a third of an inch under my left eye had begun to swell.  This swelling under the eye did not physically connect to the swelling of the eyelid and area above the eyelid.  On May 7, I went to see the doctor first thing in the morning.  She said it was an infection in the eyelid and prescribed an antibiotic.  I took an antibiotic right away and then again in the evening.  On May 8, the same day I am submitting this report, my eye was worse.  The swelling first thing in the  morning was the worst it has been and now the eye had some sort of "gunk" coming out - not badly, just overnight but this was a new symptom.  I took another antibiotic but now think it might not be helpful.  Also on May 8, the area around the injection site was inflamed and red and slightly itchy.  I put hydrocortisone cream on it.
LAB_DATA: None - may go see doctor later.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Just like my 1st dose, this 2nd dose made my arm from my elbow to my shoulder very sore starting about 2 hours after the injection. The soreness lasted for 2-3 days, gradually lessening each day. Unlike my 1st dose, this 2nd dose made my whole body experience soreness. When I woke up the next morning, I struggled to get out of bed and had to call my employer because I couldn't work that day. It was effecting all of my muscles from my neck to my calves. On 2 occassions,  I reached for an item with my right arm (non-injection arm) and had strong cramps where the tricep and shoulder muscle meet. I had to massage the cramps out. I felt like my body had been jolted in a car crash 1-2 days before. This lasted throughout the day and I felt like the soreness, cramping and immobility started to ease up around 9-10pm, So approximately 23-24 hours after it started. The next day (2 after the injection) I hopped out of bed and felt no residual effects, as if nothing had happened the day before. Throughout the day of .muscled soreness and fatigue, I experienced NO fever, chills, or nassea.
OTHER_MEDS: Daily: 10mg Crestor (statin), Complex B vitamin, Fish oil, 81mg Aspirin
HISTORY: High cholesterol, which has been controlled by my statin for 15 years

Pt cautioned about need to call EMS if increased difficulty swallowing, SOB, dizziness, GI distress. Pt's 21 year old son lives with pt and is aware of precautions.  Pt was observed until 7:20 pm , reported improvement in sx prior to leaving vaccination site.     Addendum: Dr. (Name), MD contacted pt by phone on Friday May 7. While this first vaccine gave no side effects other than a slightly sore arm, 17 days later on 4-17-2021 I suffered a TIA (Transcient Ischemic Attack). That occurred at 5:15 pm and I immediately took 4-81 mg aspirin and headed for a nearby Emergency Room. They said it was a stroke (and it did show on an MRI the next day but sub-centimeter and I was told the size of a pinhead. AT the ER the double vision in my left eye and numbness in left lips, gum and tongue were already subsiding, but the DR there gave me a Plavix and within 5 minutes I was completely back to normal (or close). I am not sure IF that first dose of vaccine had anytrhing to do with this TIA, but it might have? I had also stopped taking my 81mg aspirin several days before this TIA as I had a Periodontal appointment for insertion of an implant post and wanted to control the possible bleeding. The thoughts of my Doctor at Hospital  as well as the Neurologists was that the omission of the aspirin PROBABLY was the main cause of the temporary clotting that caused this event HOWEVER I did not tell them that I was 17 days post-Covid Pfizer vax #1 and so the possibility remains that the vaccine could have  been partially the cause of this event? As listed previously, Dr at Hospital was my Doctor and might shed some light on this and her thoughts. I felt it was important enough to report as I have heard stories of all of the vaccines possibly causing some clotting and this might fit.

I had a respiratory infection in Apr 2020 consistent with Covid-19. Testing was being rationed at that time and I wasn't tested until later.   Shortly after that illness cleared up I developed new chest pain. This was diagnosed as pericarditis and treated with NSAIDS, eventually a 3-month course of colchicine.   From approximately 3 hours to 36 hours after vaccination I experienced flu-like fatigue, joint stiffness, malaise, and chills without fever. Nothing worse than expected.   On the morning of 2 May I started to experience chest pressure and pain, qualitatively the same as my previous pericarditis. Aspirin at 1:16pm gave some relief, but I switched to ibuprofen for the next dose at 5:36pm.  3 May was fine. Not pain-free but enough that I hoped this was a brief episode.   On 4 May the pain was back. I called my primary care and scheduled and appointment for the morning of the 5th. Resumed ibuprofen.  By midnight that night the pain was breaking through the ibuprofen and I had developed an occasional cough. Presented for an emergency evaluation, spent the night being poked and scanned. Biggest concern on labs was elevated d-dimer and occasional cough suggesting a pulmonary or cardiac infarction, but an angiogram was clean.   Kept my appointment on 5th May. Tested for Covid at that time (negative), advised to watch for additional clotting symptoms, restarted colchicine.  Today is 8th May. Chest pain is somewhat managed with colchicine, but still often at 1/10.
OTHER_MEDS: estradiol valerate injection, 3mg weekly  Vyvanse 30mg daily  clonidine 0.1mg daily
CUR_ILL: no acute illness 1mo prior to vaccination

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Injection on Tuesday at 1:00 pm.  --Sleepiness/tiredness approximately 2 hours after injection which continued for the rest of the day. I went to bed around 9:00PM.  --Moderate fatigue on Wednesday and Thursday. --Sore left arm at injection site, started approximately 4 hours after injection and continued for around three days total. Quite intense initially and also the next morning, but it eased later in the day on Wednesday and was mild on Thursday.   --Chills and shivering, starting at 1:00 AM on Wednesday, which lasted approximately 5 hours. I did not sleep again after the chills started. --Fever ranging from 99.7F to 100.9F for at least eight hours. I didn't take my temperature until 6:00 AM on Wednesday, so it may have started earlier. I took 200mg of ibuprofen at 2:00 PM on Wednesday and the fever started reducing within the hour and my temperature was normal by 4:00PM.  --Headache started around 4:00 AM on Wednesday and became more intense later in the morning. Ibuprofen at 2PM helped a lot and I took a second dose of 200mg around 7:00 PM on Wednesday.  Another 200mg ibuprofen around 10:00 PM at bedtime. I had a mild headache on Thursday and took 200mg of ibuprofen around 3:00 PM.  --Nausea, a brief, intense episode around 6:00 AM on Wednesday, which eased quickly. I did not vomit, but the feeling was very intense. This episode was accompanied by light-headedness and strong  flushing and sweating. Within ten minutes, I felt much better.  --Indigestion, mild. Lasting through the day on Wednesday. Mostly a feeling of mild tension or cramps around my lower abdomen.  --Body aches, mild, and mostly in my neck and back. Starting around 3:00 AM on Wednesday and continuing through the day on Wednesday. Stiff neck and a little tender around the glands, like with a normal cold.   On Friday, I felt good again. All symptoms gone.   I stayed home all day Wednesday and did not go to work because I felt awful. I slept a lot and rested and kept very quiet. On Thursday, I felt well enough to go to work, but was very tired and had little energy. I rested at home the rest of the day on Thursday and had a nap in the afternoon.  I felt a lot better by Thursday evening.    NB: For my first Moderna COVID vaccine dose, I had no notable side effects. A sore arm around the injection site was all.

The next morning woke fine, then was seated doing some computer work and the sensation started again, accompanied by sharp, stabbing chest pain, again intestinal spasms and diarrhea.  Pulse rate was again dipping.  I went to urgent care, had an EKG, they felt it was slow so sent me to the ED.  Had another EKG and some monitoring.  Chest pain continued, and sensation that I would lose consciousness continued into the following day. The only diagnoses was Vasovagal presyncope.
