SYMPTOM_TEXT: 67 yo female with PMH of HTN, DM who has two days of left sided numbness that has progressed to left hemiparesis and dysarthria in the setting of having received the Johnson and Johnson vaccine on Wednesday(48hours prior). Patient was found to have a right parietal multifocal parenchymal hemorrhage measuring 19x36x37mm and small right temporal lobe SAH. Subsequent CTA showed thrombosis of the superior sagittal sinus and the right frontoparietal cortical veins as well has nonocclusive thrombus of right transverse and sigmoid sinus. The patient was also noted to have focal seizure of mouth and tongue and was loaded with phosphenytoin. After discussing case with neurology, nuero IR, NSGY and family it was decided to transfer the patient to sunrise for close monitoring and consideration of cerebral venous sinus thrombectomy if she worsens. I had a long discussion with multiple sisters about the risks of anticoagulation with argatroban given the IPH but the necessity given the cerebral venous thrombosis. I also discussed that argatroban is not readily reversible and that heparin is contraindicated if there is concern about vaccine induced thrombotic thrombocytopenia due to possible PF4 ab related to HIT. The patients VITT modified 4T score is 4 and she is intermediate risk for this being VITT. #Right parietal IPH, right temporal SAH and Superior saggital sinus thrombosis with nonocclusive thrombus of right transverse and sigmoid sinus -concern for vaccine induced thrombotic thrombocytopenia given johnson and johnson vaccine 2 days prior -modified VITT 4T score of 4- intermediate -send fibrinogen, d dimer, consider IVIG 1gm/kg per day for two days if high dimer, low fibrinogen and falling platelets -will start argatroban, avoid heparin until HIT ab (PF4) is resulted, if HIT positive avoid heparin -neuro IR consulted for possible IR intervention if worsens -transfer accepted by sunrise ICU, appreciate transfer for IR evaluation -continue phosphenytoin -SBP goal <150 with nicardipine and esmolol gtts -monitor daily fibrinogen, dimer, coags #AKI- monitoring uop and cr, consider renal US if worsens #DM- ISS #HTN- nicardipine and esmolol gtts for SBP <150, target 140 Patient seen, examined, labs and imaging reviewed, agree with resident note

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Approx 1 week post vaccination symptoms of Eustachian tube dysfunction (patulous) arose.   Symptoms lasted approx 1.5 weeks before resolving.  Whether covid vaccine triggered this response is hard to say.    I also  had these identical symptoms randomly occur late June 2020,  lasting nearly 2 weeks. Saw doc, and Covid test June 30, 2020 was neg.    In  Sept 20, 2020, was seen for same issue, and tested with ENT and diagnosis was Patulous Eustachian tubes.  I had not been sick with covid, that I am/was ever aware of,  or experienced any other influenza symptoms, or even a sniffle since Feb 2017.      Is it possible I was potentially covid pos, and just asymptomatic, when these symptoms  initially presented, and 1-1/2 weeks later in a doc appt no long  pos on a covid test result?   Looking back perhaps an anti body test may have been more conclusive.   In  months prior,  Jan-Feb 2020, I was around  a few folks that were sick, but not diagnosed with covid, as there was not any covid testing at that time... possible, just not conclusive.    But, now left with Patulous symptoms, unexplained and unresolved.  Either way, I am now having onset of Patulous Eustachian Tube disorder symptoms, randomly triggered, as an adult.
LAB_DATA: Nothing conclusive to date.  Have another ENT appt end of May, to follow up to Sept 2020 appointment/testing.
OTHER_MEDS: Estrogen, progesterone(HRT),   and daily multi-vitamin, vit-d, vit-c, probiotic.

Patient is a previously healthy 16 year-old M presenting with acute onset chest pain, shortness of breath, nausea, vomiting, malaise, fever and myalgia to ED on 5/6/2021 at 20:44.  He started experiencing symptoms on 5/6/2021 morning a t06:07 AM.  He received his second dose of  Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on 5/4/2021 10:: AM.  In the ED, CBC, CMP and UA was within normal limits. EKG at 20:46  and again at 21:14 showed  ST segment elevation in inferolateral leads with possible myocardial injury, ischemia or pericarditis.  Troponin 0 hour was 835 and at 2 hours 1674.  Patient was admitted to the PICU for further evaluation and management. Echo on 5/6/2021 showed normal LV systolic function with SF 31%  . Cardiac MRI on 5/7 showed contrast enhancement of inferolateral wall consistent with myo-pericarditis with small pericardial effusion.  Troponins were trended every 12 hours and plateaued in the 1800's on 5/8/2021. Patient was diagnosed with acute myo-pericarditis. Respiratory viral PCR and COVID-19 PCR on 05/06/2021 were negative. Thyroid studies were normal. ANA titer is pending. Viral serology for HbsAg was negative and HIV was non-reactive. Results for additional viral serologies for Coxsackie viruses, EBV, CMV and HHV6 are awaited. Patient was treated with  NSAIDs and Colchicine. IVIG was not given based on clinical judgement. Pediatric Cardiology was involved in patient's care and clinical decision making. Patient remained hemodynamically stable on room air throughout his PICU course. He was discharged on 5/9/2021 with Pediatric Cardiology outpatient follow up in 2-3 weeks. He will continue Ibuprofen 600 mg every hours and Famotidine 20 mg 2 times daily until his follow up.
LAB_DATA: EKG 5/6/2011 Echo 5/6/2011 Cardiac MRI - 5/7/2011 Troponin T -5/6/2021-5/9/2021 TSH, FT4 - 5/7/2021 HIV, HbsAg- 5/7/2021 Respiratory viral PCR - 5/6/2021 COVID-19 PCR - 5/6/2021

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Syncope felt hott

Intense lower back pain began about 9-10 hours after vaccine (2nd dose). Pain has continued for three full days now. Today, third day after vaccine, pain seems to be letting up a little bit. Correspondingly, the inflammation at the injection site is beginning to go down as of third day. The injection site is still tender, itchy and slightly red, and the size of the hard lump is down to about the size of a robin's egg. For the first two days the injection site was warm to the touch, quite sore and quite swollen -- what one might call a "goose egg" although not actually as big as an actual goose egg. Having had much experience with bee stings growing up, I would compare the condition of the injection site to that of a bee sting reaction. But the lower back pain is the worst I've ever experienced, more intense than the normal strain from shoveling snow or weeding, etc.. I think I did strain my back lightly an hour or two before the pain set in, but the acuteness of the pain was way beyond what the normal soreness should have been.  My observation is that my body's immune/inflammatory response to the vaccine somehow greatly amplified the inflammatory response to a slight muscle strain. I'm not a physician or scientist; this is my layman's sense of what is going on. I've not sought medical care -- assuming the muscle pain will subside in time; if it continues unabated into the next week then I may do so. In the meantime I am treating it with ibuprofen, ice and heat.  I just thought this reaction is abnormal enough that it should be reported.

LAB_DATA: On 4/202021 I received my second dose of the Moderna vaccine. I did not have any adverse reactions or symptoms beside a little soreness/tightness of the injection site (left arm). the next 12 - 48 hours I had, what I considered usual or rather symptoms that I was aware and was told by the vaccine clinic staff to expect, namely, aches, mild headache (heavy head) and a mild temp. of 100.2. I did not take anything for the first 24 hours besides rest. On the second night after the vaccine I took 500mg of tylenol as I was still achy and wanted a good nights rest. On 4/24/2021, I noticed my hands (palms) starting with the right and then the left started itching and swelling. I noticed red itchy raised bumps on either sides of my hips (obliques), and multiple raised itchy red patches starting to pop-up. This continued through the weekend and on Monday (4-26-2021) I decided to go to the doctor. The doctor confirmed this as an allergic reaction but did not conclusively say that it is due to the Moderna vaccine. I have not changed any of my medication or food/activity routines since receiving the vaccine. The doctor prescribed a steroid pack (prednisone), but after discussing with the doc, I chose to start with OTC benadryl and have the prescription a back up if it did not clear in a few days.  On Tuesday (4-27-2021) 8:00am I had a sensation of a lump in my throat with mild difficulty to breath and tightness in my chest. I decided to take a Claritin and if things didn't improve in 2 hours then I would go to the doc. However, in a few hours these symptoms cleared. All this time I was only on the OTC Benadryl at night. On Thursday, (4-29-2021) I woke up to the left side of my face swelling. I went back to the doctors office at which time the doc asked me to get on prednisone the next day and gave me a steroid shot. 45mind to an hour after the shot, I noticed the swelling come down. On 4-30-2021 I started the 6 day prednisone course. All throughout this course I was still having mild itchy, red patches pop up at random locations throughout my body. On the last day of my prednisone course, 5-6-2021, I woke up to more hives on my right elbow. On the same day at lunchtime my lower lip started to swell and I had more hives pop up. So on my way back from work I visited the doctors office again. This time the doctor confirmed that what I was experiencing could be an allergic reaction to the Moderna vaccine. He gave me another steroid shot (different from the first shot) and prescribed a 3 day course of dexamethasone. I have been on that starting 5-7-2021 and they symptoms appears to have settled. Doc prescribed an extra dose of dexa, in case the symptoms persists or come back. I am to wait 7 days after my first course to start second course. He also prescribe Benadryl to take in between as needed. So far I have not needed to take this.
OTHER_MEDS: Synthroid 175mcg Vitamin D - OTC Vitamin B complex - OTC Vitamin B 12 - OTC Multi vitamin - OTC
CUR_ILL: Thyroidectomy and gall bladder removal (6+ years ago)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 04/22/2021, a patient was determined to have pericarditis, possibly secondary to COVID-19 vaccination. The patient received his first COVID-19 vaccination (Pfizer) on 2/27/2021. The patient reported feeling poorly and presented to ER on 03/02/2021 with chest pain and dyspnea. He states the chest pain he is experienced this week is similar to the 2 episodes of chest pain he had after each of the two-step Pfizer COVID vaccination that he received in February 02/27/2021 and March 03/15/2021. He underwent a stress test on 03/11/2021 which did not show any reversible perfusion defects. Of note, the patient had COVID-19 back in October 2020 which manifested with night sweats, malaise for a few days and then cleared completely without any "long hauler" symptoms. The patient was treated with ibuprofen and colchicine.  I did not find any evidence suggesting a relationship between pericarditis and covid-19 vaccination. In clinical trials, pericarditis was not statistically significantly different between treatment arms. Other potential causes of pericarditis include atrial fibrillation.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 8 hours of injection I got very sick.  Fever went to 103 degrees, headache, severe chills and body aches.  Recovered in 48 hours. Then I felt pulsations and tingling on my left ovary which I eventually realized I was ovulating!  I've been in menopause for 4 years so I haven't felt that in 4 years.  My breasts became very tender and sore and I had faint (light pink) spotting.  This lasted several days.  2 weeks later, May 6th, I had menstrual cramps and faint pink spotting.  Although I haven't had a period in 3-4 years, I remember all the symptoms and it felt like I was getting my period.  To date, I did not get a menstrual flow.  This is a significant reaction in my opinion.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Two days after the shot, my arm was bright right around the injection site, and the rest of the upper arm had red/bluish splotches - worst of all, the outer portion of my upper arm had gone partially numb/tingly. Expecting it to be temporary, I let it go. After a week, the redness around the injection site had faded, and the splotches were less obvious but still present - and the numbness had spread to most of my upper arm. I saw my family doctor, who ordered an ultrasound to rule out a blood clot - which it did. The symptoms persist, and the numbness is spreading further down my arm. It is currently from just below the shoulder joint al the way to just above my wrist. It remains on the outer side, with the inner side of the arm remaining pretty much normal.
LAB_DATA: Ultrasound was done on 05/07/2021. The results showed no obvious blood clot.

Immediately after receiving the vaccine (within one to two minutes), I felt extremely light headed. I have never experienced anything like this before. I sat for a couple of minutes, and decided I didn't feel normal, and went up to the counter at the pharmacy and told the employee that I felt light headed. She asked the pharmacist who was standing nearby, and he said sometimes people are excited when they get the vaccine and this can happen. (I wasn't excited about getting the vaccine, but figured he knew what he was talking about.) I lived less than a mile away, so after my allotted time, even though I wasn't feeling normal, I drove home. After about 20 minutes, I felt tingling in my legs. I was laying in my bed as I didn't feel well, and looked under the covers, and I had a flat, red rash up and down both of my legs, with the rash extending to my feet. My brother is a retired radiologist in another state, so I called him. I took a picture of my legs, and sent it to him via the phone. He immediately said that he felt like I was having an allergic reaction, and to go take one or two Benadryls  immediately.  I ran downstairs and took one dose, and within 20-25 minutes the rash stopped. He asked me if I had heart palpitations, or trouble breathing, or a sense of doom. I didn't have any of those symptoms. He told me to call 911 immediately if any of those symptoms appeared. It was terrifying. After researching on the CDC website, it said even a mild allergic reaction was serious, and that I shouldn't take the second dose. Yesterday, (5/7/21), I called the CDC and chatted with someone and she suggested that I report this incident.
CUR_ILL: No illness at time of vaccine

Below is a description of the events from the incident at the event where we know that 1 individual was given an inappropriate vaccine.  The client, requested a vaccine and was assisted by the staff with filling out the consent form.  The client denied ever having received a COVID 19 vaccine before with the staff that assisted her.  The client was asked again by the vaccinator, and she again denied having received any prior COVID 19 vaccines.  She chose to have the Pfizer vaccine administered today.  When reviewing the paperwork with the staff after vaccination it was discovered that this same client had received a Janssen vaccine on 3/30/21 at a separate event.    When I arrived at the event today notified me of the event, and I went to speak with the client myself.  I found her among the crowd near the office.  When I asked her why she took another vaccine she informed me that "I wanted that shot and you have to give it to me because I'm the Chief" During this conversation it was clear to me that she was not mentally stable.  I did inform her that she could not receive any more vaccines and did my best to make certain that she understood.    When I came back to the office, I went through all the consent forms again screening for any other potential errors.   In this review another vaccination error was discovered.  I spoke with staff and the vaccinator, about the situation.  The scenario is very similar. This client filled out the consent form himself and wrote in a date of March 24 without a manufacturer in the question list provided that asked about prior covid vaccines and when the vaccinator, was with the patient she identified the date written in on the consent form and she questioned the client about it and he told her that it was a mistake and specifically denied having ANY prior COVID 19 vaccinations.  He also denied having any vaccine cards issued to him ever before.  She then appropriately drew a line through the mistaken date and initialed it.   She also confirmed with the patient that he wanted the Johnson and Johnson vaccine today and he stated he wanted the 1 shot vaccine (meaning the J and J).   I then looked the client up in the system and he is documented as receiving his first dose of Pfizer on 3/15/21.    The team is revising our operations for the vaccines and from this point forward all potential clients that request a vaccine at these events will be screened with the system prior to vaccine administration.

Fri. Apr. 23, 2021: Within 12 hours of vaccine administration, and in addition to injection site soreness and discomfort, began to notice tenderness above left clavicle, and could feel slight lump or swelling there.  Sat. Apr. 24, 2021:  -7am-8am. Lump on upper surface and tucked behind left clavicle more noticeable and tender, painful if pressed.  Was often irritated and pressed on by seatbelt when driving.   -8pm: Lump above and on clavicle a noticeably swollen, firm mass approximately 2cm across, painful to pressure or touch.  Apparently a swollen lymph node.   Injection site deltoid sore, like ?punch? to arm.  From this point on I will not document that further, other than to say the soreness peaked the following day, and lessened to non-issue rapidly after.  Sun. Apr. 25, 2021: -8am: Swollen lymph node above left clavicle swollen even more, 2-2.5cm across, constantly sore.  Painful when touched or pressed. -12pm: Pain associated with swollen lymph node above left clavicle spread laterally to lateral end of clavicle, and slight swelling to discomfort below lateral end of clavicle, in hollow between pectoral and deltoid muscles.  Remained through night.  Mon. Apr. 26, 2021: -8am: Lymph node over left clavicle still enlarged and tender, painful to touch or pressure, but not quite as bad as previous day. Irritated by seatbelt when driving. -8pm: Lymph node over left clavicle reduced in size to around 1.5cm across, still firm to touch and painful when pressed.    Tue. Apr. 27, 2021: -8am: Lymph node still swollen, about 1-1.5cm across, firm, and painful if pressed.   -8pm: Lymph node approximately 1cm across, but still firm, and painful if pressed.    Wed. Apr. 28, 2021: -8am: Lymph node above left clavicle remains approximately 1cm in size, firm to touch, but not painful, only some tenderness if pressed. -8pm: Same condition as earlier in day.  Thurs. Apr. 29, 2021 through Fri. May 7, 2021:  The lymph node above the left clavicle was pain free.  It stayed the same size, around 1cm, and is still firm enough to feel and locate by touch.  May 7 marked 2 weeks since vaccination dose 1.  Please note, patient was diagnosed as Covid-19 positive on Dec. 27 or 28th, 2020, but had a nearly symptom-free run of the disease (slight and short-lived cough, some joint pain 1 day, no fever, no other symptoms).

ALLERGIES: None.   Suffer from strong seasonal allergy to pollen of  Ashe Juniper (Juniperus ashei), probably also Eastern Juniper (Juniperus virginiana).

I feel warm and heavy all over." In response to the nurse's questions, pt stated that he had orange juice in the am, then stopped speaking. His eyes remained open and he continued to sit upright in his chair without slumping. Pt did not show any signs of distress (i.e., rapid breathing, diaphoresis, etc.).. 1st Pfizer Covid vaccination on April 1, 2021 Morning of April 2 she woke up with severe lower extremity spasticity and the inability to mobilize.   Presented to hospital April 3rd. Started high-dose intravenous Solu-Medrol on hospital day 3 and it was not until hospital day 4 that we begin to see improvement of her spasticity and ability to move her legs Felt to be acute myositis,  most likely an immune mediated post vaccination event Received 1000 mg IV Solu-Medrol x5 days Course complicated by bilateral pulmonary embolisms in setting of severe spasticity and immobility Hospitalized 4/3/21-4/13/21 Discharged to rehab, on day of discharge requiring maximal assist to stand and for transfers
LAB_DATA: Patient is quite functional at baseline with her history of cerebral palsy and can walk with a walker.  She received her 1st Pfizer Covid vaccination on April 1.  On the morning of April 2 she woke up with severe lower extremity spasticity and the inability to mobilize.  She presented to hospital on April 3 meeting SIRS criteria (fever, heart rate, respiratory rate, elevated white blood cell count) and no evidence of infection (negative UA and CXR benign).  Her exam demonstrated severe spasticity of the lower extremities with limited active or passive motion.  She had a leukocytosis of 14,000 with left shift, CRP 170 and ESR 59.  Her CK was in the 300s.  We considered a broad differential and involved neurology early on.  She had an MRI of the cervical and thoracic spine as well as a lumbar puncture that was all unremarkable for a potential cause.  Her CK continued to rise to 1700.  We started high-dose intravenous Solu-Medrol on hospital day 3 and it was not until hospital day 4 that we begin to see improvement of her spasticity.  On hospital day 4 her CK began to trend down as well and eventually normalized.  We involved rheumatology at this point who agreed that this was most likely an acute myositis given the elevated CK, myalgias, weakness, elevated inflammatory markers, and was most likely an immune mediated post vaccination event.  She did not exhibit any features concerning for inflammatory myopathy such as dermatomyositis, polymyositis, or inclusion body myositis.  HMG CoA antibody was sent and is still pending however low suspicion for a necrotizing myositis as CK was not higher.  Per recommendation of rheumatology it was felt that she would not need prolonged corticosteroids because of normalization of her CK and because pulse IV steroids can last for weeks.  Plan was for repeat CK in 2 weeks as an outpatient.
OTHER_MEDS: baclofen, diazepam, tizanidine, atenolol, bupropion, famotidine, fluoxetine, vitamin d, hydrochlorothiazide, nabumetone, Norgestim-Ethinyl estradiol
HISTORY: Cerebral palsy (very functional at baseline), hypertension, osteoarthritis, obsessive-compulsive disorder and anxiety
ALLERGIES: cimetidine - rash; acetaminophen- blisters and itchy

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I developed sudden-onset, severe, crushing pain in my left shoulder, radiating down my left arm.  This is the location where I received my vaccine one month prior. They did multiple EKGs and lab tests.  They ruled out a heart attack and pulmonary embolism.  There was no injury.  They were unable to find any cause for the pain.  They administered aspirin, protonix, and nitroglycerin.  The pain resolved after the third dose of nitroglycerin.  (I was told by the cardiology PA that this was probably a coincidence.)
LAB_DATA: 05/04/2021: They did 3 EKGs, which were all normal.  Serial troponin was normal.  D-dimer was normal.  CBC, CMP, TSH, and CRP were normal.  Chest x-ray was normal.  05/07/2021: Cardiac stress test was normal.  The cardiology PA told me she does not think the pain was caused by anything related to the heart.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient is a 69-year-old female with past medical history of diabetes, anxiety, asthma who presents with possible allergic reaction.  She had her second Covid vaccine this afternoon and within 5 minutes felt throat tightening and hoarseness.  She self administered 50 mg of Benadryl p.o.  EMS was called and she was given 50 mg Benadryl IV and an albuterol treatment.  She had a similar reaction after her first Covid vaccine and was treated in this ED and given IM epinephrine which resolves her symptoms.  She states she had many anaphylactic reactions to various allergens including vaccines.  She states this feels like how her anaphylactic reactions began.  She also notes some GI discomfort.  She denies shortness of breath, chest pain, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, or skin rash. Patient was provided epinephrine in the ED and within a few minutes noted that her symptoms were resolved. She was monitored for 4 hours in the ED with no recurrent symptoms. Patient was discharged home, will follow up with PCP and does have an EpiPen at home. Patient was feeling back to her baseline at discharge.
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer first dose, same reaction, was treated in ED with Epi at that time as well.

1. Received J&J shot in Left Deltoid- told ahead of time "People say it burns". It did burn incredibly bad--unlike any shot I have ever had-it burned like the time I had knee injection. I assumed this was "normal" for COVID.  My arm ached/hurt to move shoulder -could tell it was painful/stiff driving back again, I knew many were having "reactions" so I presumed this normal--thinking ROM issue/pain was "normal' despite my whole arm feeling such.  By 1800 that evening, my entire arm was throbbing, and starting swelling-although right handed--could see entire arm bigger than other. I wasn't able to sleep/get arm in comfortable position.  I thought this was a normal reaction-had patients to see-but touching/moving my arm hurt as bad as time I torn my meniscus.  Over next several days, swelling went down--I could painfully move my arm, but it was weak-unable to function as usual. I still thought this was normal and struggled through week as April 4-9 was Spring break.  I had trouble even leaning forward on bike because should STILL hurt--and it tapped on shoulder it would hurt incredible bad/couldn't carry daughter. Since I have higher pain tolerance- I was able to push through-however, by following week, this was no longer working--arm started swelling again.  I felt the injection was high and was talking with my mom whom  in primary care NP, and she mentioned shoulder injuries could happen if injection given too high--which is when I realized that my shoulder pain was not "all in my head".  S/p vaccination day 19 forward, it has seemed to flare as bad as initial day one and not gone back.   This is when I looked up and discovered there was also a condition called "SHOULDER INJURY RELATED TO VACCINATION" that described exact symptoms I had.     It also mentioned that damage isn't necessary should from needle--- although it was a year ago-- I had probable COVID April 2020---which could have made my immune system hyper-reactive.      I have had to call out sick April 16th because shoulder was causing pain, flushing and warm feeling.   April 19th I saw Dr-- he drew blood (I don't know what)-- didn't do full shoulder exam and referred to orthpedicc.  APril 30th I ended up calling out again as when arm would swell it made focusing at work very difficult. I saw my PCP via telehealth and she prescribed Prednisdone dose pack.   May 2nd, I  started treatment with cryotherapy machine and this was only thing that relieved pain and swelling enough to help relieve pressure.      May 7th---I saw Dr.-unfortunately, he didn't do anything because he stated a vaccine couldn't cause such type of damage to rotator cuff, didn't believe there was a condition called SIRVA and declined to treat with cortisone shot "This whole thing started with a shot-that would be inappropriate" .  He was willing to refer me to Physical therapy whom HAS heard of condition and knows how to rehab
LAB_DATA: "normal" xray 7May2021.  No further workup was done because this was referred to orthopedics, but then orthopedics decide not do do anything

SYMPTOM_TEXT: at approximately 2:13pm pt had a syncopal episode in the observation area of the clinic. Pt fell from chair to linoleum floor approximately 3 feet landing on his stomach, chest and right side of his face. an EMT in the observation area immediately called for help and attempted to rouse the patient. after being unconscious for about 15 seconds total, patient awoke and  knew his name, where he was, and what had happened. PT was sit-pick maneuvered to a stretcher in semi-fowlers position, taken to a private area and assessed. PT's head, neck and back were palpated for tenderness, deformity, injury and discomfort.  PT denied head neck and back pain. Upon assessment of mouth, pt did bite the tip of his tongue with a small amount of bleeding, approximately less than half a millimeter . Initial vital signs were taken at 2:16pm blood pressure 84/60, pulse rate 56, respiratory rate 18 lung sounds clear and equal in all 4 quadrants, pupils equal, round reactive to light, tracking motion, 4 mm in diameter.  PT questioning revealed prehypertensive, no known medical or food allergies, no over the counter or prescription medications, pt stated that he did have a  syncopal episode about 3 years ago when he was sick with the flu and bearing down on the toilet. PT stated  after he got the vaccine he sat down, was moving his arm, felt dizzy, blacked out, and woke up  on the floor. PT stated he was dizzy upon initial assessment, but other wise denied pain or discomfort. PT vitals Reassessed at 2:21pm BP 106/74, PR 60, RR18, LS clear PEARL -4mm. PT was instructed after about 30 minutes of observation to sit up for 2 minutes, PT denied dizziness or discomfort. PT instructed to stand in place for 2 minutes, pt denied dizziness or discomfort. PT  vital signs reassessed at 2:52 pm BP 134/86, PR 68, RR 18, LS clear, PEARRL 4mm. PT was escorted to his vehicle by a paramedic where his family was waiting to drive him home. PT was encouraged to seek additional medical attention as soon as possible for further evaluation. PT left clinic site at about 3:10pm

Started with a couple of hives on my back around 8pm.  In a few hours it progressed to a rash and hives all over the torso.  The next day there were additional hives on the elbows, knees, and thighs.  The rash had also spread to the scalp. The rash and hives began to fade the third day but came back that evening.  On the fourth day the hives were gone but there was still a rash in the morning.  By the mid afternoon the rash was also completely gone.  I took 2 benadryl every 6 hours while awake and that helped with the itching.  I did not take any medication between bedtime and waking in the morning.  There were times I felt a lump in my throat, but breathing was never restricted or a problem.  I did call my doctor on the second day and was told to take benadryl and call 911 if I had any issues breathing.
vasovagal syncope

I told her to keep doing that combination and in case if it gets wrose then seek medical attention.

9 hours after the shot I started to feel really groggy and sore with my left arm hurting. 12 hours in I started to feel like I had a fever so i checked it and it was 102 degree F, I was also unable to pick my left arm up due to the pain and my whole body hurt a lot. 13 hours in at about 10 pm that night I started full-body shaking violently and needed help from my parents into my room because I could not walk because my legs were wobbling so much. I felt lightheaded and the shaking continued for about 20 minutes. During this time I checked my temp again and it was 105 degrees F. Once the shaking stopped the fever and intense pain continued until 2 am when it dropped down to 102 degrees F and I was able to fall asleep. The next morning I woke at 8am with a temp of 100 degree F with the same all-over-body pain that lasted all day but the fever dropped until that night. That night it came back at 100 degrees F.  This cycle lasted from when I got my shot on the 1st until 4th when the fever stopped. The pain has subsided around the 6th. But I am currently still having pain in my left shoulder where I got my shot today on the 8th.
LAB_DATA: I did not go in for any test but I did let my primary know about the fever and the shaking.
HISTORY: I have chronic pain that affects my back, knees, neck, arms, and head. It has yet to be diagnosed but I have spent the last 8 years trying to figure out what it is and having many tests done with no results.
ALLERGIES: No medication allergies, allergic to peanuts and lactose intolerant

I was not having any congestion, allergies, or asthma during the week leading up to the COVID vaccine. The day after the injection, I had flu-like symptoms but no congestion or asthma. The following morning, I woke up with severe body aches and a pulse-oximeter reading of 85% oxygen, and my regular reading is 95% or higher, even off the ventilator and on room air. I remained on my night ventilator and turned up my oxygen from my usual 2 liters to 5 liters. I used my airway clearance devices and had a breathing treatment, but my pulse-oximeter reading didn't improve at all. I was nauseated and took Odanestron. I had severe body aches and took Acetaminophen. It didn't help. I took my temperature, and it was 103.7 an hour after taking the Acetaminophen. I went to the emergency room and was admitted to the ICU with pneumonia. I have had pneumonia several times in my life, but this was an extremely sudden onset
LAB_DATA: On 04/04/21 My white count was elevated. My x-ray showed pneumonia. I was negative for COVID.  I was hospitalized from 04/04/21 to 04/12/ 21. Blood and sputum cultures were negative for viruses and were initially negative for bacteria. Eventually, a culture revealed pseudomonas. I am very diligent with my respiratory, ventilator, and trach hygiene. I had not had pseudomonas since 2012, and the onset of pneumonia was more gradual then.  While ventilator use is a risk factor for pseudomonas, I fear that the COVID vaccine overwhelmed my immune system. Immune system disorders are also a factor for pseudomonas.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had a sore arm the first two days which is normal.  But on day 4, I started with a very bad sore throat and then had difficulty breathing. and couldn't stop coughing. When I was a child I used to get asthma, it has been 30 years since I have had asthma.  I went to urgent care and they tested for strep throat and Covid 19.  I tested negative for both.  A week later I called urgent care because I could not stop coughing and was having difficulty breathing.  They prescribed a very low dose of Prednisone for 6 days.  That did not help so I finally went to my asthma and allergy doctor.  He prescribed the correct dose of  Prednisone which I am now on day 3 taking.  As well as an Inhaler which helps as well and a gel tablet to help with cough.  I feel like I am finally on the rode to recovery but I am nervous about taking a 2nd Pfizer Vaccine.  My doctor also told me I should not take the 2nd Vaccine until 10 days after I am finished with Prednisone.  That will be passed the 42 day recommended time frame to get the 2nd Vaccine.  I don't know if the vaccine caused these breathing problems but I do know that I was 100% healthy and hadn't had breathing difficulty for 30 years.  That is why I think it may be possible that the vaccine triggered this.  I felt it important to report.
LAB_DATA: Strep and Covid-19 tests both tested negative.

On 4/14, had a series of rashes on left side of face - eye lid, eye brow, forehead and well into the scalp.   Following a visit to Dr,  He confirmed this to be Shingles and referred me to the Ophthalmologist as the Shingles had affected eye surroundings. I have been prescribed and taking Valacyclovir, Gabapentin, and Prednisolone eye drops to treat the Shingles.   Into week 3, Shingles rashes have all healed, blisters have all crusted out and cleared, however nerve pain continues in the head and around the eyes. The ophthalmologist suspects this to be post-Shingles effect, i.e., Postherpetic Neuralgia. My current condition results in Insomnia during various nights, and itchiness/tingling sensations, for which I have to apply cold/wet compress and Calamine Lotion to provide temporary relief.  As a result of above following the 1st COVID vaccine, I have postponed my 2nd COVID-19 (Pfizer) vaccine to 5/22. However, my confidence level to proceed and get this 2nd vaccine on 5/22 is low at this time, until CDC is able to let me know whether there is a link between the COVID-19 vaccine and this causing Shingles in rare cases, to help me avoid a repeat of the stressful experience after the 1st COVID-19 shot.  I would greatly appreciate a callback or an email.
LAB_DATA: In-person consultation confirmed Shingles Eye exam to confirm no 'internal' damage to eye by Ophthalmologist  Blood test to rule out kidney issues Continued visits planned - next on 5/21 to review latest condition

Developed hypertension and pounding heart beat/palpitations starting Jan 15, 2021.   Symptoms worsened over several weeks; necessitating 2 Emergency room visits on Feb 1 and Feb 20.  BP upon arrival ED ~ 200/110.  Pt has no history of hypertension.  Over the next several months, hypertension slowly resolved.  Several antihypertensive medications used to obtain blood pressure control. By May 8, 2021, pt reliably normotensive.  The pounding, hyperdynamic heart beat has persisted.  Pt can feel a regular, hyperdynamic heart beat, as much as 24 hours/day.  It is reliably worse while supine at night.  Pounding heart beat's severity has improved, slowly, over time, but has not resolved.  Pt being treated with beta blocker for symptoms.  There has not been any arrhythmia.  There is very intermittent chest pain best described as feeling "inflammatory";  at times there is chest discomfort with palpation over the sternum.  No dyspnea.
LAB_DATA: EKGs: Sinus Brady (baseline), non-specific T wave inversion;  Echos X2 - normal EF.  Right atrial pressure elevated at 8 mm-Hg, no evidence pulm htn;  Troponins negative at ED visits:  Chest Xray Normal;   CT PA gram - Normal;  ESR and CRP - Normal;  Chem Panel and CBC normal:  Renal Artery US negative for Renal artery Stenosis;  Abdominal US - normal - no evidence of AAA;  Cortisol, Metanephrines normal;   Renin undetectable; Aldosterone normal.

Vaccine Adverse Event Report  May 8th, 2021. Patient, had an appointment for his 2nd dose of Pfizer Covid 19 vaccine May 8th 2021 at 10:00am. His first dose of Pfizer Covid 19 was at our Pharmacy on April 16th, 2021. At around 10:15am, patient came in with his fianc�, who is a doctor at pediatric department, shown on her name tag. After processing the paperwork needed for vaccination, Pharmacist on duty, went over the VAR to ensure the provided information was adequate before it was ready for my intern to administer the shot. Patient looked fine as I was able to have a brief conversation with him while waiting for the shot. Due to some insurance issues that needed to be resolved, at 10:40am, pharmacy intern, took the patient to Patient Health Room for immunization. At 10:45am, I was ringing up a prescription at Terminal 42 when hearing the word, Help, coming from the Patient Health Room. Within seconds later, the door was opened as I was running out the pharmacy toward the Patient Health Room to see what happened. The patient was lying on the floor, unconscious, while his fianc� was calling his name asking whether he was okay and rolled him to his side and supported his head. I reached into the cabinet and prepared to administer an EPIPEN to the patient, meanwhile, pharmacy technicians, asked and dialed 911. As his fianc� kept calling his name, the patient gained consciousness. I asked intern what had happened to clarify whether it was a reaction due to the vaccination or not. Meanwhile, the patient's fianc� stated this event was not unexpected. Patient was able to talk and confirmed he was fine. Unfortunately, it appeared that the patient bruised his nose and forehead with slight blood from a minor cut. We instructed the patient and his fianc� to stay in the room and offered assistance upon request until EMS arrived. Patient's fianc� requested an ice pack for his bruise. Later on, the patient appeared to be shaking, so I asked the fianc� whether it was okay to give him some GATORADE. His fianc� also requested a glucose meter to check his blood sugar. The EMS arrived within minutes and patient was transported to hospital Before they were leaving, I asked the fianc� if there was anything she would like us to do as well as offered a follow-up. She declined the offer. I also asked briefly if she could share his medical condition, but the fianc� only disclosed that the patient has needle anxiety. The EMS also said that they will take it from here, and there is no additional action needed from our end at this time. Each team members who were involved in the event wrote reports and kept them filed in the pharmacy records.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Was fine until I stood up at approximately 9:30pm. Immediately got very fatigued, head started hurting. Bent over to pick something up and my back hurt around where my lungs are; it hurt to breathe. Within 15 minutes I could barely stand up. After about an hour of the symptoms intensifying, I started to get a low grade fever. I took something for the symptoms (alka seltzer daytime pill), but went to bed shortly. I started waking up off and on around 6 (I normally sleep in until noon). At 7am, I woke up feeling like I was on fire. I grabbed my thermometer from my nightstand- it read 104 degrees Fahrenheit. I tried to open my medicine but I was so weak I couldn?t do it myself. I walked downstairs and woke my mom up. She took my temperature and it read 103 since I was no longer in my bed warmed by my body heat. She opened my nighttime alka seltzer and gave it to me along with 800 mg ibuprofen. I went to bed with nothing but a sheet and a cooling pillow. At some point my mom came in and handed me my water but I don?t remember it, however it helped cool me down when I fell asleep with it in my bed. When I woke up at 11, my fever was only 100 and it was the only symptom I had. When I got out of bed at 1, I was fever free. I?ve been fatigued the rest of the day but the fever hasn?t returned and I?ve been taking 325 acetaminophen every 4 hrs.

Here,  rheum/neuro workup largely negative. Her course has been c/b multiple DVTs and Aflutter that has resolved. So far, workup for AMS and fevers have been extensive -- BEM, LP, MRI, thora, bronch w BAL were unremarkable. The patient has been monitored off abx without hemodynamic changes. She did not improve despite various abx administered and did not really respond to seroquel for her delirium. At one point, the husband was considering hospice because nothing had improved her clinical status. Given her rheumatologic hx and declining mental status after the vaccine, the patient was treated with methylpred 1 daily x3 and this dramatically improved her clinical course. She began to wake up and per the ICU, was AOx2-3 at one point, whereas she had not responded even to painful stimuli at one point. She still did have some hypoactive delirium. At this point, she was deemed stable enough to be transferred. Our phsyicians were following her through the admission, was not aware and speaking again until 5/5/21.   Currently she is undergoing epilepsy workup and is still hospitalized.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The second night after the shot I was awakened out of a sound sleep at 3AM  with a pain across the entire top of my upper chest (at the top of the breast region) it was a though someone had turned a 2x4 on its side and was standing on it.  I was clammy and had some hives on my back and hips. I sat on the side of the bed I stretched my arms did some yoga type moves trying to see if being less active the day after the shot maybe had my back a little tight causing the pain.  I chewed two tums thinking that might help to get rid of the pain even though I knew it was worse than heartburn. After 15 mins at 3:15 I woke my husband to let him know it was not going away and that I was not sure what was going on but just in case I did not want to be ridiculous and sit there and have a heart attack. I'm not one to run to the doctor, I'm very healthy but thought to myself this may be more serious.  My husband ask about calling for help and I said lets just see what happens and just know if I need help then you at least know my symptoms now . I woke the next morning and felt much better and made a joke about all the crazy people being right stating "they are trying to kill us"  Later in the week on Thursday playing tennis I felt me left arm going numb, I shrugged it off to hitting the ball hard and it never crossed my mind about anything else. Two weeks to the day on Sunday Morning I woke with a migraine that made me feel I was going to throw up.   The news just came out about J& J and the few family members that knew about my adverse reaction urged me to report and go to the Dr.   I'm currently dealing with a bruise (I usually don't bruise badly) on my left front chin- I could have hit it on something who knows but it has been there now over a week.
LAB_DATA: I have no idea where to start but family and friends are pressing me to go get checked out - any helpful information of where to start would be helpful

Over the next day or so those discolored areas mentioned previously began blistering and turned into open sores. She went to her primary physician where they completed blood tests, which returned as normal, and a physical exam. The physician's conclusion was a shingles-like reaction. Over several weeks the blisters and sores healed leaving a discolored area. The patient mentioned that the areas mentioned did not itch or produce any hives. They were only painful. The physician recommended the patient go back to the pharmacy where she received that first dose so she could discuss the reaction with the pharmacist and obtain the lot number, so this incident may be reported. The patient reported to me that she did in fact have a varicella infection when she was younger. She has numerous photos taken  if you decide to investigate further. She has received influenza vaccinations in the past with no reactions.

Shingles.  I received the second dose of covid vaccine on Wed, April 28. Three days later, Saturday May 1,  I woke up with intense abdominal pain, spanning the entirety of my stomach, and wrapping around my right oblique and kidney area. I had thrown out my back one week prior,  assumed this was more muscle pain, and treated it as such.   The Monday following, May 3, I went to the chiropractor, still in intense pain, but also with a tingling sensation on the affected area, sensitivity to the touch without pain. I assumed that I had burned myself with the heating pad.  Wednesday a rash began to form in the affected area. My pain was nearly gone, I no longer felt muscle tightness, and assumed that the condition was resolving itself, and that the rash was heat rash from the heating pad.   Friday the rash was redder and my abdomen showed signs of significant swelling. I still thought this was muscular, that perhaps I had pulled the abdomen, treated with ice and decided to visit Orthopedic urgent care Saturday.  Saturday the pain had increased. I went to Urgent care, and was told I have shingles. I asked if the covid vaccine could have caused shingles to flare, was told "theoretically", but thar we do not really know enough to say whether the vaccine contributed, or whether it was coincidence.  At home, I read a bit on the covid vaccine qnd shingles, saw what appeared to be anti-vaccer propaganda, but also read about this self-reporting system...so, I thought that I might as well submit my info.
LAB_DATA: No medical tests, just medical examination.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am a 72 year old woman in very good health. I received the first Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination on March 8, 2021 and everything was fine. I then received the second vaccine on March 29, 2021.  The day after I received the 2nd Pfizer vaccine I developed scalp psoriasis. (I only had this once about 6 years ago). I fought it for 2 1/2 weeks. It cleared up on April 21, 2021.  That evening my right wrist  began to itch terribly. Within a couple hours my right hand and arm swelled and got red up to just below my elbow. I went to the doctor 2 days later on April 23, 2021. I had gotten poked by a cat claw the day this started and was told it was cellulitis even though cellulitis does not itch like that and there was no pain nor soreness. I have had cats for over 35 years and been poked, scratched, and bit many times with no reaction. Two hours after leaving the doctor?s office, the rash and swelling progressed up to the inside of my elbow. I went to emergency and was told again it was cellulitis. They gave me iv anitbiotics and sent me home with a prescription for amoxicilan. Three hours after returning home, my left hand started itching. It then also became inflamed and swollen like the right hand. The swelling went down within 2 days and I continued talking the prescription for the 7 days. I had a follow up visit with my doctor on April 30, 2021, and all looked well. Two days later the itching began again on my right arm in the bend of my elbow. This was May 3, 2021.  I went back to emergency and was admitted to the hospital where they were giving me iv vancomycin. I had no pain nor fever. On the 3rd day, May 5, 2021, my right knee and left foot began itching. Both areas then became inflamed and swelled.  I saw 6 doctors during this hospital stay and they were all perplexed. They sent an Infectious Disease Specialist who said it was a reaction to the original iv antibiotic that I was given on April 23, 2021, for what was diagnosed as cellulitis.  I was released on day 4, May 6, 2021.  I never felt comfortable with any of the diagnosis. I was never in any pain, had no fever, nor any other indications of cellulitis except for the rash and swelling. Cellulitis does not go from the right hand to the left hand, to the right elbow, to the right knee, to the left foot! I didn?t agree with the diagnosis of being allergic to the first antibiotic I was given. The only thing I have ever shown a reaction to is Tetnus. Granted we can develop allergies in life but this is a stretch.  Upon returning home I called a friend of mine who said that her husband had the same thing happen to him after the second Pfizer vaccine! He scratched the effected area so much he broke skin. He went his doctor and she was smart enough to guess it was a reaction to the vaccine but his scratching may have caused a bit of cellulitis. He was given an anibiotic ointment to use on his scratches and told to take Zyrtec during the day and Benadryl at night. That cleared him upI   I have to wonder now how any people are experiencing this after being vaccinated and their doctors are misdiagnosing it as cellulitis. My experience resulted in days of misery and probably around a $20K hospital bills for nothing. I think that people and doctors especially, need to know that the vaccine can cause this to happen so it can be treated correctly without what I was put through.  We are not being given all of the information that we should know. I realized no one wants to start a panic about being vaccinated but this is just WRONG. Wrong and causing a lot of unnecessary misery along with costing tens of thousands of dollars in unneeded medical costs. I can be reached by phone to discuss with more detail . Please give this serious consideration. Thank you!
LAB_DATA: Hospitalization.  Xray of right elbow to confirm no bone infection and ultra sound to check for blood clots. Multiple blood tests performed over 3 days.

The headaches and neck pain continued every single day for 6 weeks before I finally reached out to my PCP regarding my symptoms on 4/21/21. She prescribed me prednisone, which made the symptoms worse and more symptoms developed including vertigo with nausea and pressure with a burning sensation deep behind my left eardrum and on the left side of my neck at the base of my skull. I had a follow-up on 4/28/21 due to worsening symptoms. My headaches and neck pain were getting extremely painful. The pain feels like a nerve pain that goes down the left side of my neck, into my left shoulder join, down into my left scapula, and down the left side of my spinal column. The headaches come and go all day every day at random locations. The left-sided neck pain and pressure is constant. I had labs and a CT of the head done on 4/28/21 (WNL). On 4/29/21, I developed left-sided facial numbness that lasted the entire day and I went to Medical Center. Dr. recommend I go back to my PCP and have her order an MRI of my head and neck.  My next appointment is this week. I still have slight numbness to the left lower facial area and lips along with headaches, neck pain and pressure. Today, I can barely turn my head due to the severe neck pain.

The week of 3/28/21 I began to feel numbness on the right side of my body, in my genital area.  By 4/18/21, the numbness had spread into my right glute, which was completely numb.  On Sunday, 4/25, I had a sudden onset of all of the following:, the numbness had spread upward and downward and the right side of my body was partially numb; vision in my right eye was blurry; my right eye hurt, and felt swollen; my pupils were unequal; my neck was stiff; I was dizzy; and I could not speak properly.   I felt very floaty.  These symptoms waxed and waned, together, for several hours at a time, getting progressively worse each time.  My lucid periods also got progressively worse.  I went to my PCP who ran bloodwork and referred me to a neurologist, who I could not get an appointment with until July.    On 5/3/21, I was admitted to the ER based on the recommendation of the triage nurse who heard my symptoms and their duration.  The ER ran a bunch of tests and found nothing.  I went home and over the next few days entered again into several nonlucid states.  I believe my body was getting closer and closer to death.  I began taking my temperature with a reliable thermometer, and found it was dropping to 93-95 during my symptomatic periods.    I found help from alternative doctors who immediately intervened, and continue to monitor me.   The doctor I listed on this form was my ER doctor.
LAB_DATA: All of the tests ran by the ER - Bloodwork, EKG, CT Scan.  I am happy to share the results of any or all of those with you.
OTHER_MEDS: I was taking nothing at the time.
HISTORY: I have back pain that had largely subsided by the time I received the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Developed Bell's Palsy in right side of face.  This is the second time I have had Bell's Palsy; the first time was about 10 years ago.   The ER physician said it was very unusual to get this twice in a lifetime.  I was diagnosed with Bell's Palsy about a month after my second Pfizer Covid-19 shot and thought it could be related since this adverse event did happen during the trials.

I felt well for the 8-9 hours after the shot, around 8pm that  evening, a headache and mild fever started.   By 1am, fever, chills, increased headache, severe joint pain were in full swing, muscle almost felt like they were on fire.  Even rolling over in bed HURT.  Fever got as high as 101.8 (I usually am around 97.6 or so).  Symptoms started to abate by mid morning, but I was essentially useless until that evening.  By May 6, I felt like I had a really bad hangover all day, then was mostly recovered by that evening.  It is now May 9.  I have a long history of knee/arthritis pain, and am generally a rather active person, but since the second dose, my knee pain as well as my hands to a large degree, have been extraordinarily sore and painful.  My knees in particular, while the symptoms were really peaking, I experienced some very acute,atypical pains a couple times in both knees that seem to keep recurring 2-3 times per day, as well as exacerbated, continual soreness and general pain when I am active.
LAB_DATA: None yet, I am considering getting checked over this coming week if symptoms don't seem to be improving.
ALLERGIES: Some yogurts give me hives, sensitive to ibuprofen and aleve

SYMPTOM_TEXT: For 2 days, typical arm soreness, flu-like symptoms with significant muscle pain and general weakness and malaise. However, on the 5th day, EXTREME abdominal pain, left side. Pain level up to 9. Incapacitating. Two visits to urgent care. This was in March before any info came out about adverse blood clot events for the J&J vaccine, so the doctors were not really interested at the time that I had just gotten my shot. They gave me antibiotics, thinking it may be diverticulitis (diagnosis based on symptoms only - no diagnostics - it was the doctor's "best guess"). Pain did not subside, only got worse. 4 days later I could barely move, abdominal pain was extreme. Went back to clinic and they did a PET scan to check for diverticulitis. There was none; PET scan revealed nothing out of the ordinary. So they told me they had no idea what it was and sent me home. PET scan reading by the doctor notes specifically that blood/vascular was not able to be observed because no contrast or dyes were used. Bottom line was over 10 days of extreme abdominal pain 5 days after receiving the shot. I've never experienced anything like that before.
LAB_DATA: PET scan 3/21/21 - nothing unusual noted.  Blood urea Nitrogen - normal CBC (complete blood count) with differential - normal Creatinine - normal Electrolytes - normal Urinalysis - normal (specific gravity, UA was slightly high at >1.030) Hemoglobin A1C - normal (5.5% HB1AC and 112 mg/dl glucose)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 81 year-old female patient in otherwise good heath received her first dose of BNT162b2 (Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine), administered in right arm on 02/02/2021 (Lot Number EL9264) for COVID-19 immunization.  Concomitant medications include: Losartan and Atenolol.  Vaccine was administered at approximately 5:00 pm at a drive through location.  The vaccination was administered by the County Health Department.  Shortly after receiving the vaccine (but while still at the facility), patient started experiencing a bulging of the right eyelid.  Patient did not immediately recognize that this may have been related to the vaccination. Over the next several days, patient started experiencing additional symptoms including drooping of right side of face, drooping of right eyelid, difficulty closing right eyelid and weakness on the right side of the face.  This was unusual and on 02/10/2021, patient contacted her primary care physician who referred her immediately to Emergency Department for evaluation.  The following tests and procedures were performed by the ER: Basic Metabolic Panel, CBC Hemogram, Troponin, eGFR and CT Head w/o Contrast (reason facial drooping).  Diagnosis: Bell's Palsy, Adult.  On 2/11/21, patient had a follow-up with primary care physician.  On 02/11/2021, the patient received prednisone (10 mg once daily for 5 days) as treatment for the Bell's Palsy.  The reported events required visit to Emergency Room on 02/10/2021 with follow-up at Physician's office on 02/11/2021.  Reporting is delayed because patient understood that the adverse event had already been reported.  At a later date, patient requested a copy of the adverse event report for her records but learned that the adverse event actually had not been reported.  Report is being filed by a contactable family member.
LAB_DATA: 02/10/2021: Basic Metabolic Panel, CBC, Troponin, eGFR and CT Head w/o Contrast (reason facial drooping).  Diagnosis: Bell's Palsy, Adult
HISTORY: None, patient is in otherwise good health.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few seconds after shot, pt became pale and immunizer asked if he was ok. His muscles tensed and shook a little and he passed out, falling slightly to the right. The technician was able to place herself between him and the floor and slowly lower down, leaning  against the wall of the pharmacy.  By this point, about 30 seconds at most had passed, and pt was awake and cognitive, but had no recollection of passing out or how he had gotten to the floor. He did know his name and where he was, but was breathing heavy.  We took his blood pressure at this point and it was 82/46 with a pulse in the 40's as well.  Pt refused ambulance and we had him continue to sit on the floor.  Patient mentioned he had this type of reaction in past to other vaccines (not stating what), though only telling us prior he had "slight dizziness once".   He also stated he had not had anything to eat or drink that am so we got him a snack and some water.  Patient continued to breath deeper as we suggested and stay on the floor as we called mgmt from the store.   We took blood pressure about 10 minutes later and it had gone up to 117/71.  and then again 10 minutes later and it was 121/69.  After 30 minutes total, pt asked if he could stand and leave.  He stood with no dizziness and said he felt "fine".   We called patient approximately an hour later at his residence to make sure he got home ok and patient stated he had no other symptoms at that time and continued to feel "normal".

Patient presents to clinic for symptoms of illness which began 5/5. She received her second Moderna vaccine around 6:00 pm on 5/5. Late evening into early morning on 5/6 patient developed nasal congestion which has worsened over the last several days. She also reports watery eyes, post nasal drip, scratchy throat, headache, sensation of fullness in ears, low grade fever with tmax 100, chills, and malaise. She feels that her symptoms have peaked today. OTC medications include advil cold and flu which has not helped with symptoms Pain with headache 6/10 currently, has not taken anything today.   Patient was treated for upper respiratory infection with cough and congestion.  Symptoms likely due to viral infection. At this time supportive care is recommended. This includes drinking plenty of fluids, rest, and continuing to monitor symptoms at home. You may take Tylenol for your headache, decreasing pain level should help reduce BP. Monitor BP closely at home. Do not use decongestants as they may increase your BP. You may take a product approved for HTN patients ie Coricidin.   Patient was advised of the following quarantine instructions:  There are multiple viral infections that could be causing your symptoms. However, due to the current global pandemic with COVID-19 and increase in community spread, it is in your best interest to self-quarantine. It is recommended to return after 10 days since symptoms first appeared AND 24 hours with no fever without the use of fever reducing medications AND COVID-19 symptoms have improved.  A test-based strategy is no longer recommended to determine when to discontinue home isolation, except in certain circumstances. Only follow up in the ER if you are in respiratory distress or your fever continues to elevate. In order to protect your family, you need to stay as isolated as possible within your house, ideally in your own room. You can take Tylenol to help lower your fever, drink plenty of fluids, and get rest until your immune system fights off the virus.  For more information, please visit www.cdc.gov  Guidance provided from https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/if-you-are-sick/end-home-isolation.html.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The injection site felt "achey" immediately after the injection and this discomfort lasted several hours despite my gently massaging the band-aid site. My left arm felt "heavy" for the rest of the day. Within 18 hours of vaccination, I was awaken from sleep shaking violently. I thought that someone was shaking me violently. When I realized that my body was shaking so, I wrapped myself in a comforter; then I passed out or went back to sleep. When I was aware of myself again, I was too hot wrapped in the comforter and removed it. I was very concerned about what had happened to me so I moved slowly getting up and starting my day. I live alone so there was no one to help or advise me. For the next few days, I rested often, not sleeping, just feeling the need to lay about.   By week 2 after the injection, I was "dragging" but not sleeping. When I laid down, my mind roamed about, when I tried to read or engage in meaningful activities were not successful.  By week 3, I have full-blown insomnia. I go to bed at 4 am to be awake for hours while in bed, then being exhausted during the day. I am normally active, but I do not have the stamina to do what I love such as mowing my own lawn and working in garden. My heart rate jumps to 122 after 10-20 minutes of activities when in the past I could work steadily for 40 minutes and my heart rate never get above 90 beat per minute ( I  wear a charge 2 watch that monitors exercise parameters.) I had to stop to rest up to 4 times to complete the yard work that I could normally complete in less than 40 minutes.  Currently, I have "hay fever" symptoms: itchy runny nose, tickle in the throat with dry cough, tired, runny eyes  and frontal headache; I take benadryl  and other allergy medicines. I have poor sleep habits.
Heart palpitations. Racing heart. Palpitations so strong they made me cough. Last 4 days.

A few minutes after getting the vaccine I had a fast heart rate and my throat felt like it was closing up. I let the personnel know and the EMTs hooked my up to O2, blood pressure and EKG, I had a jump in heart rate on EKG every couple minutes and my blood pressure started off very high. It gradually decreased. I then had the feeling after about 20 minutes that I needed to poop. I was unhooked and went to the bathroom. I proceeded to have diarrhea for the next 2-3 hours. The EMT let me go home after about 40minutes of total care because my oxygen level never dropped below 100.  I would have feelings of flushing and throat tightening until about 6pm. They did not reoccur after that. I have never had a reaction like this before to a vaccine or any medication.
LAB_DATA: None. Just the EKG and the blood pressure monitoring at the facility by the Emergency personnel.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received her first dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine on 04/11/2021. Patient arrived for her second dose on 05/09/2021. The mother of the patient was in the car and mentioned that she registered the patient under her own birthday.  When changing the patient's birthday to the correct date, it was recognized that the patient was only 17 years old and not yet approved for the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Received shot on 04/23/21 and symptoms began on 04/27/21 in the morning: sensitive to touch on left side of the body and the pain did not go away throughout the day. Went to the doctor on 05/05/21 and he diagnosed me with Shingles. He prescribed Valacyclovir 1GM (generic for Valtrex 1GM) tablets, 1 tablet 3 times daily for 7 days. Pain continued, worsening at night; went to see a dermatologist on 05/06/21 and he prescribed SSD 1% Silver Sulfadiazine Cream 50 Grams to apply topically twice a day on the blisters. Condition has since started to improve. Some blisters are scabbing over. Nerve sensitivity is terrible still. I am still continuing to take 3 Aleve PM (220mg) before going to sleep.

BP and heart rate were normal when checked. Patient able to sit up and drink a little water after 1-2 minutes. Patient was able to walk out of the clinic with no assistance after that.

Patient was given her shot, she got up and sat down in the nearest observation chair, then immediately said she was dizzy and thought she was going to pass out. I went to her and she repeated that she was about to pass out. When her head started to roll back I was able to hold her by her shoulders. Her eyes rolled back and her head dropped back and she started convulsing. She lost consciousness for about 10 seconds. When she came to she didn't know what was happening. She was very sweaty by this time. I asked if she had a history of seizures or had ever fainted before and she answered no. EMS was called. I checked her BP and it was 84/41. The patient tried to stand to assist with finding her husband in the store but I told her she had to sit until EMS arrive. We offered her water and orange juice and she asked for both. When the husband got there we asked him if she has a history of fainting or seizures and he said this has happened multiple times, mostly as a result of seeing blood. He said she hasn't had seizures but she has had tremors when this has happened. I checked her BP again and it was 116/88. She was feeling a lot better. EMS arrived and she was stable by that point. They recommended that she go to the hospital, but patient opted not to go.

Please note this was after my first dose (to which I also had a pretty extreme reaction and was quite sick for a couple days, but I had virtually No reaction to my second vaccine). I want to report that now, in May, several months after my vaccine course completion, I am again experiencing COVID arm. These are the same dots, in virtually the same places on my body. This just started today. I simply want to report that this appears to be a recurring reaction. Today is only the first day I?m finding the dots (spreading slowly). I will see my SAME doctor tomorrow which I saw in January for the rash originally. I have also documented the rash day by day through photographs which I?m happy to share for the purpose of research. I?m also happy to release my notes from my doctor?s visits if they are requested.

With in seconds of receiving the vaccine I became really dizzy and light headed, my heart also began to race and my whole body felt really warm. The doctor was really nice and let me lay down and wait the suggested 30 minutes.  I also felt like I was stoned for 3 weeks after receiving the first dose. The best way to describe it would be a sense of tiredness/ fog like feeling with on and off feeling of vertigo whenever I moved my head to the right.  The vaccine also messed with my menstrual cycle. My period came 10 days early and I spotted 3 days prior to it actually starting with is abnormal for me. I also became very dehydrated, I drink more than 80 ounces of water day day so this was also a cause of concern. My lips became discolored, I had patched of red spots on my upper lips which I associated to the vaccine. I went to the doctor and they assured me that it wasn't due to the vaccine and brushed off the above mentioned. They said I may have an active case of COVID and they tested me. The results came back negative. Along with these symptoms I also experienced headaches and chills and a sore throat with in the first 3 days of receiving the vaccine, which was expected. Immediately after the patient received the vaccination he stated that his arm felt numb. This seemed to concern him greatly although I reassured him that this reaction had been reported to me on other occasions and it was transient. I checked his blood pressure and pulse, both of which were normal, and he waited for about 20 minutes before returning to work where he received the shot. He returned to the pharmacy approximately 15 minutes later and stated that he felt dizzy, nauseous, and had blurry vision. His forehead felt cold and clammy to the touch and he was sweating. I had him sit, and checked his pulse again (still normal). He stated that his chest felt "cold and tired" but he was not having difficulty breathing. After observing him for some minutes I gave him a 50mg dose of Benadryl in case the reaction was allergic in nature. I observed him for at least 15 more minutes were he seemed calm and was able to speak on his cellphone to family so they could come and pick him up. In my opinion he seemed improved by the time he left but I counseled him to seek medical attention if his adverse feeling worsened. The patient was able to walk out of the Walmart without assistance. I called him at home around 5:20 pm and he sounded very sleepy but he had not yet had to seek further medical attention.

On 4/30/2021 I recieved the Covid-19 vaccine and on 5/1/2021 I started with upper abdominal pain and nauesa. It went away and came back on 5/3/2021, went away and came back on 5/5/2021 with the pain and nausea intensifying. I went to ER on 5/6/2021 at 1 am. When I arrived to the ER they proceeded to do bloodwork, also ordered an x-ray to ensure that my lungs were not causing an issue due to where pain was located. After the labs came back they saw my liver numbers were extremely high, so then they ordered a CT scan with contrast. CT scan showed everything to be normal. They then determined I needed to be admitted due to believing I had a stone in my bile duct, Gallbladder was removed in 2019. The MRI was done at 7pm on 5/6/2021. The results were recieved on 5/7/2021 and showed my bile duct was clear of obstructions. They continued to monitor my liver numbers and I was released today 5/9/2021 due to my numbers continually decreasing with instructions to follow-up with my PCP to have labs run again to ensure my numbers remained on decline to the normal range. I was also instructed to do the adverse event reports as to them not having enough data to determine if the vaccine may have been the reason for my high numbers. My PCP had just had my yearly labs done on 3/16/2021 and my liver numbers were normal.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the fourth of May, evening after the second shot, I started to get body aches and a sharp pain in the injection site. So I took some Aleve and went to bed early at 9:00pm. At 3:00am I woke up with vomiting, diarrhea, a fever of 102.2, chills and worse body aches. I threw up everything I tried to drink, even water and Vitamin Water. Trying to eat anything produced the same result. I live alone, so I thought I was prepared for getting sick, but it just kept going on for days. I called an ambulance Friday morning when vomiting and nausea still had not passed. I wasn't having diarrhea anymore, but I wasn't keeping anything down, so that's probably why. My urine was brown and sticky, I had dropped weight and was missing multiple days of work. I was given Zofran IV and fluid IV in the ambulance, first bag of three. The ER gave me two bags of fluid before I could produce a urine sample, which was very dark orange. Then "one more for the road" as they said. They did a CT scan of my abdomen with and without contrast. They prescribed Zofran. The next day I went back to the ER with more nausea and vomiting, severe stomach and abdominal pain, and still dark orange urine. I was taking the Zofran as prescribed, and the also prescribed Prilosec.
LAB_DATA: Various blood tests and urine tests in the ER, a CT scan, swab for Covid testing for some reason (long q-tip in nasal cavity, very unpleasant).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initially, I had no symptoms, but on 4/29/21, just over two weeks after my second vaccine dose, I had blood drawn for my routine diabetic health check-up and my live function test results (ALT and AST) were alarmingly high. For several years, these numbers have been right in the normal range (13/16, 22/18, etc.) but at this post-vaccine blood test, my ALT was 386 and AST was 108. My diabetic specialist was horrified and immediately thought I had liver damage or disease. But with such good liver function numbers as recently as February 2021, I was doubtful. I have experienced no other symptoms of liver damage or disease, and have not changed any medications, foods, or habits. I can only conclude the elevated numbers were the result of the vaccine. Furthermore, a week after the 4/29/21 blood test, on 5/6/21, I had those blood tests repeated, and my liver function numbers decreased: ALT was 211 and AST was 85.
LAB_DATA: Blood test on 4/29/21 and one week later, on 5/6/21, another blood test. (See details of results above.)
